Commentary: Roach starts with a good length ball on the fifth stump line, KL shoulders arms.
Goes fuller this time, Rahul goes for the drive but mistimes the ball towards mid on as he gets an inside edge.
FOUR! First one of the game. Slightly fullish ball again. KL opens the bat face this time to place this through the point region to open his and India's account.
Shortish ball in the channel this time, KL covers his timbers and lets this go to the keeper.

FOUR LEG BYES! Looks to make the batsman play but this is pitched on middle and shapes further down the leg side. KL Rahul looks to tuck it fine but misses. The debutant keeper, Hamilton, goes to his left to stop it but can't. It goes towards the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Fullish ball blocked towards mid on this time by Rahul. Good start this for India.
Off the mark on the first ball. Good length ball coming into the body, Agarwal does well to tickle it towards fine leg to take a single.
Length ball in the channel outside off. KL lets it go as the ball shapes away after passing him.
Fullish ball on the fourth stump line this time, places towards gully for nothing.
Superb ball! Came in sharply with the angle after pitching around the fourth stump line. KL looks to shoulder arms but is hit close to the box. No harm done though.
Good length ball outside off this time, he leaves this one to the keeper without any trouble.
Fuller but too wide to make KL play. He leaves it alone.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal covers his stumps and let this go to the keeper.
Fuller ball outside off, pushed straight to the point fielder.
Beaten! Fuller length ball in the channel outside off, Agarwal has a poke but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Another full ball around off, blocked nicely this time.
Fuller ball on the pads this time. Agarwal flicks it nicely through the deep mid-wicket region. The two went for the intial runs quickly and a lazy effort from the fielder means that they get three.
Length ball outside off, KL lets it go.
Outside off on a length, it swings back in a bit towards Agarwal. He shoulders arms to it.

FOUR! Edged and just short! Agarwal survives! Good length ball around off, it nips back in after pitching. He looks to fend at it but gets an outside edge at it and the ball goes to the left of second slip where Holder is positioned. He dives forward and to his left but it falls short and goes through the slip cordon towards the third man fence for a boundary.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Length ball on middle and off, Agarwal defends it off his back foot.
FOUR! Much better this time. Full ball just outside off, Agarwal leans into the drive and pushes it through the cover region for a boundary. That will give him some confidence.
On the pads of Mayank, he looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the pads.
Full ball around off, Rahul blocks it out towards Roach off the front foot.
Beaten! Roach is getting some movement here. Fullish again around off, Rahul goes for a push at it but the ball swings away and goes past his blade into the hands of the keeper.
Full and on the off pole, defended out.
On the pads of Rahul, he looks to flick this one but misses. It hits his pads and the ball rolls towards fine leg for one. Agarwal on strike.
Beaten! This time it is Agarwal. Another fullish ball outside off, this time Mayank goes for the push towards the off side but the ball whizzes past his bat.
Outside off, full. Mayank gets bat on ball with this one and pushes it towards the mid off fielder.
Bad line this time by Gabriel. Down the leg side, Rahul flicks it towards deep backward square leg for a couple. The bat turned in the hand of Rahul a bit but he still manages to put it away.
Shortish ball around off, comes into the batter and hurries him into the shot. Rahul manages to somehow block it.
Good length ball coming into the batter, Rahul pushes it towards point.
FOUR! Great shot this by Rahul. Full and around off, Rahul pushes it towards the gap at point and cover. The ball races to the fence for a boundary. Rahul looking comfortable here.

Full ball and on the off side, Rahul leans into the drive and pushes this though mid off. The fielder from mid off hares after it and keeps it in the field as the batters take three. With that three, Rahul gets to 2000-run mark in Tests.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks it towards square leg for a double.
Full ball around off, defended to the fielder at cover.
Length ball outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
Another length ball outside off, Rahul does not fiddle at it.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! Caught! Beauty from the skipper and Rahul is out of here! Cornwall takes the catch at second slip and it is unlucky thirteen for Rahul. Holder pushes this one on a length just around off and gets it to straighten after pitching. Rahul plays at it off the back foot and gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball carries into the laps of Cornwall and he takes a dolly. Master stroke from the skipper and he has got his team an important wicket here.
Full ball around off, Pujara pushes it towards cover-point. Maiden wicket over for the skipper.
Length ball outside off, defended by Agarwal.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Beaten! Another length ball around off, Agarwal goes to fend at it but the ball swings away and goes past his outside edge.
Full ball around off, pushed to mid off by Agarwal.
Full and straight again, Agarwal pushes it down the ground. Roach bends to his left and gets a hand to it but the ball goes behind him and the batters steal a single.
Outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Length ball around off, pushed to point by Agarwal off the back foot.
Holder mixing up his length. This time full attacking the off pole, Agarwal blocks it out but at the last moment.
Beauty! On a length around off, Holder pitches it around off and gets it to straighten. Agarwal looks to play at it but does so inside the line of the delivery.
Similar delivery. These deliveries are reminiscent to the delivery Holder bowled to get Rahul out. Agarwal is beaten this time too as he bails out of the shot at the last moment.
Full ball around off, pushed to mid on.
Length ball around off, pushed back towards Holder off the back foot.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Beauty by Roach! This one is pitched on a good length, it nips back in sharply. It goes just over the middle and off pole of Pujara. Pujara is beaten all ends up which doesn't happen that often.
Fuller one on off, Pujara blocks it out.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara lets it go.
Good length ball on the stumps this time, Pujara blocks it towards mid off.
Length ball on off and middle, blocked nicely again by Pujara.
Holder getting great movement here off the new ball. Full ball outside off, luring Agarwal into the drive. He goes for it but the ball shapes away from him and he is beaten by this all ends up.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Length ball on the off pole, Agarwal pushes it back to the bowler.
Educated edge by Agarwal. Another one short of a length outside off, Agarwal plays at it with soft hands and away from the fourth slip fielder. The ball goes underneath him towards third man for one.

Beaten! Pujara this time. Holder bowling beauty after beauty here. Short of a length on the off pole, Pujara looks to defend at it but again inside the line. Holder trying to lead the attack for his side against the visitors.
This time outside off, Pujara leaves it alone. Holder looking menacing here.
Good length ball outside off, Agarwal pushes this to point.
Fullish on off, Agarwal looks to defend but gets an inside edge and the ball rolls towards square leg. He calls for a couple but settles for a single seeing the fielder haring at the ball.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball just outside off, Pujara solidly blocks it onto the ground.

Mighty, mighty close! A good leave by Pujara. This one pitches on a good length outside off and nips back in. Pujara knows exactly where his stumps are and lets that through. It is very close to the stumps for his liking but he survives.
Blocked towards mid on off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle and drifting down leg, Agarwal blocks it towards the leg side.
Similar one by Cornwall, blocked towards short leg by Mayank.
Floated on off this time, Mayank defends it onto the ground.
Full and floated around off, Agarwal drives this one through mid off but Chase runs to his left and puts in the dive. He saves at least two runs for his side.
This time Mayank pushes it straight to Chase at mid off.
Single off the last ball as Agarwal plays this floated one on the leg side towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball outside off, Agarwal leaves it alone.
Fuller this time, pushed towards cover by Agarwal.
Another fuller one outside off, pushed towards the fielder at cover.
On the pads of Mayank, he looks to glance this one but misses. It hits him on the thigh pad and goes towards the leg side.
Another one wide outside off, Agarwal does not fiddle at it.
Outside off, on a length. Mayank lets it through to Hamilton.
Floated on middle, Pujara blocks it out towards mid-wicket.

Floated on middle and leg, Pujara pushes this one through mid-wicket and sets off. The fielder there gives it a chase. The batters run quickly and complete three easily. He is off the mark with that shot as well.
FOUR! Slammed over mid on. Full and floated on middle and leg, Agarwal lifts it over the fielder at mid on for a boundary.
The batsman has driven it through mid-on.
Floated on middle and off, pushed back towards the bowler.
Flat one just outside off, Agarwal looks to fend at it but bails away at the end.
Shortish ball in the channel, left alone nicely by Pujara.
Another shortish ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone again.
Length ball on the fifth stump line this time, Pujara is not going to fiddle with this one either.
Shortish on the hips, tucked towards square leg for a run.
Fuller outside off, pushed straight to cover.
Bumper this time but too high. Agarwal ducks under it.
Cornwall continues. Flat on off and midlde, Pujara comes down the track and blocks it out.
Change of pace by Cornwall and Pujara as a result chips it towards mid on but well short.
This time on the pads, Pujara guides it towards mid-wicket and takes a double.
The batsman has driven it through mid-off.

OUT! Caught! Cornwall gets his first Test scalp. Shamarh Brooks takes it! Experts say that you should not cut a spinner on the first day of a Test match and maybe that's why. This one was short and around off by Cornwall, Pujara rocks back and looks to cut it past point. The extra bounce does him as he does not get decent enough contact on it. It goes straight to Brooks at point and he takes a sitter there. India 2 down now on 46 and the hosts are back into the game.
Floated around off, pushed to point by Kohli. End of a successful over by debutant Cornwall.
Fuller on the fifth stump line, Agarwal leans forward to push this towards cover.
Full on the pads this time. Agarwal blocks towards the leg side.
Good line and length from Holder. Agarwal lets this go as he sees the ball shape away from the him.
Good length around off, blocked towards point off his back foot.
Fullish on the pads again, Agarwal strokes it straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Another fullish ball around off, blocked nicely by Agarwal.
Short around off to Kohli. He blocks it towards Cornwall off the back foot.
Floated around middle and off, Kohli pushes it out.
On middle and leg, the ball turns in and Kohli is beaten by the spin. He misses his flick to get hit on the pads.
Floated around middle and off, Kohli blocks it out presenting the full face of the bat.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed to mid on off the front foot by Kohli.
Another one on the pads, Kohli flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Length ball on middle and off, Agarwal looks to block it but gets an inside edge on it and the ball hits his pads.
Outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Full and outside off, Agarwal leans into the drive and pushes this through the cover region. The fielder hares after it, gobbles it up near the fence and the batters take three in the meanwhile.
Short of a length around off, Kohli defends it out off the back foot.
Fuller this time on middle and off, Kohli hits it into the ground.
On middle and leg, Kohli looks to flick this one but misses to hit hit on the pad.

On the pads of Kohli, he flicks this through fine leg. The ball trudges towards the fine leg fence. The batters take three as the fielder gives a chase and fields it just inside the crease. 50 up for India!
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

NOT OUT! Too much turn on it and Kohli survives. Cornwall floats this one outside off, on a good length. Kohli prods forward to block it but misses. It spins back in and hits Kohli on the pad. The Windies players appeal loudly but nothing from the umpire. After having a talk with his bowler, Holder goes for the review. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no edge. Ball Tracker comes into play, pitching outside off, impact in line, going down leg. Good decision by the umpire. West Indies lose their first review of the match.
Floated around off, blocked off his back foot by Kohli towards short leg.
Another one outside off, Kohli blocks it confidently.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
The ball strikes the batsman very low on the pads. Two runs added to the total. The Umpire signals Leg Bye.
Outside off, left alone.
Good length on the fourth stump, pushed towards cover.
Good leave! Shortish ball around off, came in sharply towards Agarwal who does well to sway it away as he falls to the ground.
Short and on the pads, Kohli flicks it off  his pads towards fine leg and takes a single to get off the mark after the fifteenth ball.
On the pads of Kohli, he misses his flick and that has struck him on the thigh pad.
blocked off his back foot this time by Kohli.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed towards square leg.
Floated around off this time, blocked by going back into the pitch by Kohli
Flighted on off, pushed towards point.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Beaten! Shortish ball, going away from the batsman. Goes past the outside edge.
Good length ball in the channel, Agarwal lets it go.
Wide outside off, left alone again.
Length ball around off, blocked off his front foot.
Good length ball around off again, blocked towards mid off. Fifth maiden over from Holder. He is in great rhythm here.
Short and outside off, Kohli looks to hoick this over mid on but is early into the shot. Maybe it stuck into the surface there.
Floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Outside off, floated by Cornwall. Kohli looks to defend this off the back foot but is beaten.
Floated on middle and off, Kohli prods forwards and blocks it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Another one full and floated outside off, Kohli defends it towards point.
Holder starts with a bouncer to Agarwal off the first ball. He ducks under it and lets it through to Hamilton.

FOUR! Good shot this one by Agarwal. Full and outside off, Agarwal just pushes it through mid off to the fence for a boundary. Welcome runs for India. First boundary after 64 balls for the Indians here.
Outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Fuller this time around middle and off, Agarwal pushes it down the ground.
Another length ball outside off, left alone by Agarwal.

Edged but safe! Agarwal plays this fullish ball outside off with soft hands. It goes uppishly to the left of the fielder at gully but drops just short. The fielder does get a hand on that but the batters take one.
FOUR! Crunched! Short outside off, Agarwal punches this off his back foot through cover-point for a boundary. He is looking in good nick here.
Floated on fuller length, pushed back to the bowler.
Fuller outside off, Agarwal strokes it towards mid off who dives to his left to stop the ball.
Gets behind this loopy ball to tuck it around the leg side.
Good length ball, flat just outside off, Kohli pushes this towards the off side.
Another ball which is a touch short, this time on the pads of Agarwal. He flicks it towards fine leg for a single and retains strike.
Full and down the leg side, Agarwal plays the paddle sweep and the ball races towards the fine leg fence. The fielder there runs to his right and does well to cut it off. Two runs taken.
Short and outside off, left alone by Agarwal.
Agarwal prods forward and pushes it back to Chase.
Another full and floated one on middle and leg, Agarwal pushes this towards mid on for a single.
Kohli prods forwards to this full and floated ball outside off to defend it.
Leading edge induced off this short ball outside off. It goes towards point but no one is there and the batters take two.
Short and on middle and off, pushed towards the bowler off the back foot.
This time fuller, Agarwal blocks this one out.
Tossed up around off, Agarwal defends it out.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Shorter this time, Agarwal punches this one off the back foot towards the bowler.

Agarwal beaten by the turn here. He comes forward to this floated ball around middle and off but he misses his flick as the ball turns and is hit on the pads. A stifled appeal from the Windies but nothing from the umpire.
Shortish ball, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single. That was very close to the short leg fielder.
Fuller on stumps, blocked nicely by Agarwal lunging forward.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Quicker one this time around off, blocked again.
Goes back to the crease to defend this off his back foot.
Another shortish length ball going down, padded away by Agarwal to go unharmed into LUNCH ON DAY 1.
Loopy ball on middle to start with, Kohli tucks it towards the leg side.
Another loopy ball on off and middle, pushed straight to short leg.
Comes forward to block this fullish ball onto the pitch.
Loopy ball around off, pushed towards mid-wicket.
First run of the session. Fuller on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted ball on the pads, Agarwal taps it fine down the leg side for a couple.
Shortish length around off, coming into Kohli who looks to work it down the leg side but is late into the shot. Gets hit high on the thigh pad.
Another shortish ball, Kohli taps it towards mid-wicket off his back foot.
Short again, this time onto the body, Kohli hops to block well.

FOUR BYES! Another bouncer on the body, angling away from Kohli. He looks to pull this one but the ball rises a bit and Kohli misses to get bat on ball. Looked as if it touched the gloves there. No, not really! A lot of away movement as the ball passed Kohli's attempted pull. Good call from the umpire there.
Fullish ball on the pads this time, Kolhi flicks it towards backward square leg to get a couple this time.
Shorter ball to finish the over. Kohli hops to block again.
Agarwal comes down the track to this tossed up ball and pushes it towards mid on.
Tossed up on the pads this time, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Shortish and on middle and off, defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Tossed up around off, pushed to the fielder at cover.
On the pads of Agarwal this time, Agarwal flicks this towards the leg side.
Floated on middle and leg, Agarwal blocks this out onto the pitch.
Good length ball just outside off, Kohli goes for the push towards cover but gets an inside edge on this one. The ball rolls towards the fielder at mid-wicket.
Down the leg side, Kohli looks to flick but misses and the ball goes to Hamilton behind the stumps.
FOUR! Full and on the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards mid-wicket with nonchalance, his trademark shot and that races to the fence.
Length ball on the body of Virat, he tucks it towards the leg side.
Similar ball, similar result. Virat defends this length ball towards mid-wicket again.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Driven through mid-off by the batsman. One run added to the total.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Kohli has punched the ball off the backfoot. The ball races to the boundary. Four runs has been signalled by The Umpire.
Kohli defends this one off the back foot.
Short of a length ball outside off, Kohli opens the face of his bat and guides it towards third man for a single.
Length ball on middle and off, blocked by Agarwal off the back foot.

FOUR! Beautiful straight drive by Kohli. Full and on middle and off, Kohli leans into the drive and pushes it back past the bowler for a boundary. 50 stand up between these two. Important stand for India.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shortish ball around middle and off, defended well by Agarwal.
Bouncer this time by Gabriel. Agarwal does well to sway away from it.
On the pads of Agarwal, he flicks it towards mid-wicket.
On the pads of Kohli, he pushes it towards mid on.
Shortish and outside off, Kohli looks to cut this one but misses it altogether. Cornwall getting some good bounce off the surface here.
On the pads of Kohli, he flicks it towards mid-wicket for a single.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
On the pads of Agarwal this time, he flicks this one towards square leg for one. 100 up for India with that single. 100 up for the visitors with this single.
The batsman has driven it through mid on.
Outside off, left alone by Agarwal.

EDGED AND FOUR! Too close for comfort here for Agarwal as he edges towards his half ton. This one was pitched around off and it nipped back in. Agarwal looks to defend but gets an inside edge on it. The ball hits his thigh pad, goes over the wickets and to the fine leg fence.
Outside off, left alone again by Agarwal.

FOUR! Fifty up for Agarwal but in streaky fashion. This one was full and outside off, Agarwal goes for the drive but gets an outside edge on it which goes wide of third slip and into the third man fence. Third fifty for Mayank Agarwal in Test matches and he will be looking to carry on from here and get to a big score.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Agarwal defends this one out back towards the bowler. End of an eventful over.
Full and on off, Kohli pushes it towards mid off.
Another fuller one around off, Kohli drives it through covers. It does not have the pace on it to get to the fence and the batters take two as the fielder mops it up.
Outside off again, but this time shorter. Kohli does not fiddle with it.
Bouncer this time, nipping back in towards Kohli. He does well to evade it.
Holder mixes it up and goes fuller this time. Kohli pushes it towards mid off.
Down the leg side by Holder, Kohli tries to flick it but misses.

NOT OUT! Agarwal had a hunch that he did not nick it and he was right. The decision has been overturned. Roach bowls this one  around off, it swings away a bit and Agarwal misses his defensive shot. The Windies players from the slip cordon appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Roach didn't seem all that confident but is happy to see the finger lifted by the umpire. Agarwal quickly has a chat with his skipper and goes for the review without any hesitation. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no spike. A successful review for India and Mayank's wicket is still intact. The sound was of the bat hitting the pad, as confirmed by Ultra Edge.
Full ball outside off, pushed to the fielder at cover.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fuller ball, punched straight to mid off by Agarwal.
Fuller length outside off, Agarwal pushes this towards wide of the point fielder to get a couple of run.
Good length ball around off, pushed straight to mid off.
Shortish lengh around off, Kohli blocks it off his front foot.
Length ball around off, Kohli hops to block this one onto the pitch.
Fuller on the pads this time. Kohli flicks it nicely through mid-wicket. The ball was racing to the fence but Darren Bravo hares after it and stops. Three run taken.
The batsman has stood up on his toes to play that one.

OUT! CAUGHT! Catch number two for Cornwall at first slip, wicket number two for skipper Holder in this match. Agarwal can't do much after the half ton. A superb shortish ball on the fifth stump line, the ball shapes in as Agarwal looks to push this one towards the off side but it shapes a tad bit away as it comes closer to the bat. It takes the outside edge and goes straight to the safe hands of Cornwall. West Indies get a timely breakthrough.
Bumper outside off, Rahane ducks under it.
Good length ball around off, Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, Kohli shoulders arms again.
Fuller and straight, Kohli strokes it towards mid on.
Good length around off again, closer to Kohli. He taps it towards point.
Fuller ball on off, Kohli flicks it straight to mid-wicket.
Good length around off this time, Kohli lets it go.
Shortish ball around off, blocked towards cover.
Another short ball into the batsman, blocked again by Rahane.
Good length ball outside off, pushed to the man at cover.
Another fuller one around off, pushed again to the man at cover.
Outside off by Holder, pushed towards mid off by Rahane.
Shortish and on the body of Rahane, he pulls this one towards square leg by getting on one leg and takes a double to get off the mark.
Tossed up on middle and leg, pushed towards backward square leg for one by Kohli.
Floated just outside off by Cornwall, Rahane blocks it out.
Another floated one outside off, pushed back towards Rahkeem.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Full and floated around leg, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Rahane prods forward and defends it straight back to Cornwall.
Length ball outside off, Rahane covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Bumper on middle but too high. Rahane ducks under it.
FOUR! Top shot! Shortish ball around off, going away from Kohli. The skipper guides this one between gully and point to get a boundary. Played that very late.
Shortish one again, Kohli hops to blunt it to point.
Another bumper around off. Kohli hops again to tap it towards the off side and call for a quick single. Good response from Rahane means it was completed easily.
Another shortish delivery on the fifth stump line, tapped towards point by Rahane.
Loopy fuller ball on middle, pushed straight to mid off.
Flighted on middle and off this time, worked straight to mid-wicket.
Around off, blocked well by Kohli.
Comes forward to block this one towards point.
Flatter but too wide outside off. Kohli lets it be.
Length delivery on middle, stroked straight to mid-wicket off his back foot.
Shortish ball in the channel outside off, blocked nicely by Rahane.
Fuller this time from Holder. Rahane flicks it nicely through mid-wicket. The fielder chases the ball to stop it, he does so but can't stop the batters from taking three.
Shortish again. Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball again, Kohli blocks again.
Bouncer in the ribs of Kohli this time. Kohli hops to block it well.
Full around off, Kohli pushes this straight to mid off.
Floated on leg pole, Rahane blocks it towards the leg side.
Another one floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Loopy delivery on the off pole, pushed towards the man at mid on.
Tossed up by Cornwall on middle and leg, Rahane flicks it towards mid-wicket for one.
Shortish this time on the leg side, Kohli goes onto the back foot and takes one as he pushes this one towards square leg.
FOUR! Crunched! First one for Rahane! Short ball outside off, enough time and room for Rahane to go back and time his cut superbly through cover-point.
Short ball outside off, Kohli stands tall to push it towards point.

EDGY FOUR! Fuller ball outside off, Kohli goes for the drive but gets a thick outside edge. The ball races through the slip and gully cordon and to the fence. That was not an intentional shot but Kohli will take it.
Shortish ball outside off again, tapped towards point.
Fuller this time just around off, pushed towards cover.
Mixing it up here Holder. Short and outside off, Kohli gets on top of the bounce and pushes it towards point. This delivery was similar to the one which got him dismissed in Antigua.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards mid off by Kohli.
Flat and on off, pushed towards cover.
Another one on floated and off, pushed back towards Chase.
Flat and full outside off, pushed towards Chase off the front foot.

Just short! Shortish ball this one by Chase, Rahane goes back and cuts it towards the fielder at point. It goes uppishly but falls just short. The fielder does well to grab onto it and no runs are taken.
Chase goes full again, played out by Rahane.
Another one tossed up around off, pushed towards mid off. End of a good over from Chase.
Back of a length around off, Kohli punches this straight to point.
Another shortish ball on middle, Kohli looks to push off his back foot but mistimes it on the leg side.
Length ball in the channel outside off, Kohli lets it go.
Good length ball just outside off, pushed towards the man at cover. The early swing that Holder was getting seems to have gone away since a long time now.
Length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on off the back foot by Kohli.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Kohli.
Shortish this one outside off, Rahane pushes it towards point.
Tossed up around middle and off, Rahane pushes this one down the ground.
Rahane blocks this fuller one towards the off side.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Full and floated on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.

Close! Presence of mind from Rahane saves him. Chase bowls this one shorter and on the body. Rahane looks to defend it with soft hands and is hit on the glove. The ball rolls onto his thigh pad and towards the stumps off his gloves. Just when the ball was close to hitting the wickets, Rahane turns around and pushes the ball away with his boot.
Length ball outside off, Kohli looks to push but gets an inside edge onto the pads. Kohli wanted a run but is sent back by Rahane.
Length ball outside off, Kohli pushes this straight to point.
Outside off in the channel on a good length. Kohli watches the ball go to the keeper.
FOUR! Classic Kohli drive! Overpitched ball outside the off stump, Kohli leans into the drive and drills this through covers for a boundary. No chance for any fielder.
Fuller ball on middle, Kohli walks across to push this towards mid on.
Beaten! Cut him into half. Good length ball in the channel outside off. Kohli looks to block of his back foot but the ball sneaks past the bat and pad. Lucky not to edge or have his stumps shattered.
Fuller ball around off, Rahane dances down the track to force this towards mid on.
FOUR! Rahane's turn to display the cover drive now. Flatter ball outside off, Rahane goes back in the crease to cream the drive through the cover region. A very good shot that.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Comes down the track to block it back to the bowler.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flatter on full, pushed towards the cover fielder.
Shortish ball outside off, Kohli lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Kohli is into the groove. Fuller ball outside off, Kohli leans into the drive and strokes it through the covers for a boundary. One short of his half century now.
Fuller on off this time, Kohli comes forward to push towards cover.

Shortish ball around off, Kohli tucks it towards point to get a single to reach to his half century. His 22nd in his Test career. A fighting knock this from the Indian skipper. He would look to convert this one into a big one.

Huge Appeal but not given. Fuller ball on the pads of Rahane who goes for a whip but can't get bat on ball and is hit flush on the pads. An appeal from West Indies but nothing from the umpire. Holder asks his bowler regarding the review but doesn't go for it. Looked to be going down leg.
Shortish ball outside off, left alone.
Flighted ball on short of a length, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Flighted and fuller, pushed towards the leg side again.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Fuller one, pushed towards mid off.
Comes behind the line of the ball, blocked nicely.
Fullish ball around off, blunts this one back to the bowler.
Shortish length coming into Rahane who blocks it nicely off his back foot.
Length ball around off, blocked towards cover.

FOUR! Poor line from Gabriel and he has been punished by Rahane. Fullish ball outside off. Rahane leans into the shot and times the cover drive brilliantly to earn another boundary. Gavaskar on air is asking Gabriel to bowl a bouncer in the West Indian accent.
No says Gabriel as he dishes a length ball. Leaves it alone.
Length ball around off, closer to the body of Rahane. He deadbats it towards the off side.
Fullish ball on off, Kohli drives this through mid off with superb timing but can't beat the diving Kemar Roach. A half stop from Roach means Kohli can get a run though.
Coming down the track to push towards the bowler this time.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Nicely done! Straight ball around off, Rahane guides it towards the third man region to take a couple.
The batsman has driven it through mid on.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Flatter and fuller, blocked coming forward by Kohli.
Loopy ball around off, Kohli blocks this one off his front foot.
Loppy ball on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Flat around off, Kohli gets behind the line of the delivery to block.
Shortish ball, Kohli pushes this towards point.
Another shortish ball on the pads, Kohli tucks it fine down the leg side for a single. AND THAT IS TEA ON DAY 1.
Shortish ball around off, pushed through cover by Kohli. The point fielder dives to stop but can't get his hands to it. The ball goes towards sweeper cover. Three runs taken.
Length ball outside off, defended by Rahane towards mid off.
Fuller ball, Rahane goes for the drive but  gets an outside edge. Played with soft hands as the ball goes towards the second slip fielder.
FOUR! Sweet timing! Bumper but the ball doesn't rise much. Rahane swivels to pull this towards deep square leg. The ball races to the fence quickly.

OUT! CAUGHT! Roach gets his first wicket as Rahane has been caught behind. Exactly the kind of start the hosts were after. Length ball outside off, Rahane is rooted to his crease as he pokes at the ball. The ball kisses the outside edge and goes straight to keeper Hamilton who is not going to miss out on that. Body blow this for the Indians.
Beaten! Tentative push from Vihari on the first ball which is in the channel outside off. Lucky not to edge that one.
Flatter one on middle, eased towards mid-wicket.
Another fullish ball, flicked but short leg stops it well.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Fuller on the pads this time, timed straight to mid-wicket.
Flatter one on the pads, worked towards square leg.
Shortish length coming into the batsman, Vihari covers his stumps to leave this one alone.
Shortish around off this time, blocked off his back foot towards the off side.

NOT OUT! Comfortably going down leg. Waste of a review from Holder and the Windies have now lost both reviews. Holder was not convinced but it seems like his bowler was adamant for that one and the skipper obliged. A length ball outside off, coming in with the angle, Vihari looked to flick but missed and was hit on the pads. Roach appealed and was the only one confidently doing so. Holder was not too keen but went with his bowler. Alas. Ball Tracker shows it to be missing leg. By a fair margin too.
Length ball around off, blocked towards cover.
Fuller on off, blocked off his front foot by Kohli.

FOUR LEG BYES! That looks close but the umpire is not interested this time. No reviews left for West Indies there and Roach was suggesting as if it hit high on the pads. It was a length ball which Kohli looked to block by coming forward but he was late into the shot and he gets hit on the pads. It went through keeper Hamilton and Cornwall at first slip. The ball trudges towards the third man fence while the Windies team are appealing. The Ball Tracker shows that this was hitting the timber but the impact was umpire's call.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
Loopy fullish ball on the pads, worked towards square leg for a run. He is off the mark with that single.
FOUR! Hammered down the ground. Fullish ball on off, Kohli powers this down the ground.
Another fuller ball, pushed towards the bowler.
FOUR! Another powerful boundary from Kohli. Fullish ball on middle and leg, Kohli times this through the diving mid on fielder to get another boundary. He is scoring runs briskly here.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Fullish ball, pushed straight to the bowler by Vihari.
Bumper but too high. Vihari ducks under it.
Length ball outside off, left alone this time by Vihari.
Good length ball around off, blocked towards cover.
Length ball around off again, left alone by Vihari.
Another length ball, this was coming into Vihari. He looks to block this towards the leg side but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket.
Flatter and shorter, flicked straight to mid-wicket by Kohli.
Fuller loopy ball this time, again finds the mid-wicket fielder.
FOUR! Deft touch from Kohli. Flatter on the pads, Kohli goes back and tickles this one fine down the leg side, using his wrists. The ball races to the fence.
Flatter and fuller, drives it straight to mid on.
Goes back to the crease to tap this one towards short leg.
Defended by Kohli by going back in his crease.
FOUR! Driven firmly by Vihari! Length ball around off, Vihari leans forward and powers this one straight down the ground to get his first boundary of the innings.
Fullish length outside off, the ball flies off his outside edge towards third slip but falls short of the fielder there.
Length ball around off, Vihari stays in his crease and blocks.
In the channel outside off, blocked nicely by Vihari.
Good length ball in the channel closer to the body, blocked by coming forward by Vihari this time.
Fullish ball closer to the off pole, blocked towards cover by Vihari confidently.
Starts with a fullish length ball, Kohli lunges forward to push it towards the mid on fielder.

Another fullish ball around off, Kohli punches this nicely through the covers. The cover fielder shows some footwork as he stops this with his foot. Kohli sees the opportunity of the second run and hares back for it.
Full outside off, pushed towards mid off.
Bouncer outside off, Kohli ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on the body, Kohli hops to tuck it towards square leg to take a single.
Bumper down the leg side this time, Vihari ducks under it.
Loopy ball on the pads, tucked towards the leg side for a single.
Another flighted ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Flighted ball on off, defended by Vihari comfortably.
Flatter on the pads this time, tucked closer to the short leg fielder.
Flatter around off, pushed towards mid off.
Comes down the track to work it towards mid-wicket.
Bumper from around the wicket to get past the outside edge of Kohli. This was pitched on middle and leg, it went away from Kohli who hopped to push it towards the off side.
Another bumper but Kohli is up for the challenge. Swivels to pull this nicely by rolling his wrists. Gets a single.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Vihari shows full face of the bat to time it towards mid on for a couple.
Another bumper from around the wicket. Vihari does well to sway away from it.
Another bouncer from Holder. Left alone by Vihari.
Shorter ball on middle, hops to block well.
Flatter on middle, pushed towards mid on for a single.
FOUR! Just short of the fence or else this was half a dozen. Fullish ball, Vihari dances down the track to lift this one over the mid off fielder to get a boundary.
Comes forward to this flatter delivery around off, blocked.
Flatter ball on middle, tapped towards mid-wicket.
Shortish ball, tapped towards point.
Shortish ball, Vihari looks to tuck it towards the leg side but the short leg fielder gets the ball and throws it towards the stumps. Vihari, however, was quick to get back in.
Shortish ball angling in towards Kohli, pushed down and onto the ground.
On the pads this time, Kohli flicks it towards square leg.
Length ball just outside off, pushed straight back towards mid off.
Bouncer by Holder on the leg pole line. Kohli ducks under it and lets it go.
Misfield and a couple of runs allowed. Shortish by Holder, Kohli cuts it through point and a couple is taken.

Peach of a delivery this by Holder. Kohli looks to defend this length ball off the back foot but does so inside the line. It whizzes past the outside edge. Oohs and aahs from everyone in the Windies team.
The batsman gets to the pitch of the ball and defends it.
Flatter on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a run.
Flighted on off, Kohli lunges to block.
Flatter and fuller, pushed towards mid on for a run.
Short around off, Vihari goes for a cut but is beaten.
Comes forward to this middle stump delivery to block off his front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Holder strikes for the third time in the day. Kohli is outta here! Superb delivery from the West Indies skipper to find the outside edge of the Indian skipper. Length ball, shaping away from Kohli who lunges forward to push it with hard hands but the ball finds the outside edge and it carries to keeper Hamilton. The umpire is checking for the front foot but it is absolutely fine. Kohli has to walk back. India lose their skipper and West Indies are into the lower middle order now.
Wide outside off, left alone by Pant.
Another ball outside off on a good length, left alone by Pant again.
Goes slightly fuller this time, bowled around off. Pant pushes it towards point.
Shortish ball this time around off, Pant taps it towards gully.
Bumper on the body this time. Pant didn't know what he was doing there as the ball takes the edge and flies towards the fine leg fielder. Falls short as he takes a run to get off the mark.
Loopy fullish ball on middle, blocked by Pant.
Flatter this time, looks to block but is hit on the pads.
Flat on middle and leg, Pant pushes it back to the bowler.
On middle, blocked back to the bowler.
Comes forward to power this through mid off but the ball goes from the inner half of his bat towards mid on.
Fuller on off and middle, blocked well by Pant.
Fuller ball around off, pushed straight to cover.
FOUR! Whipped! Fuller ball on the middle from Holder, a rare one. Vihari flicks it nicely through mid-wicket to earn a boundary. That was timed brilliantly by Vihari.
Length ball around off, tapped towards point.
Shortish ball around off this time, Vihari again blocks it well off his front foot with soft hands.
Shortish ball on the body, blocked off his back foot this time.
Beaten! Beauty from Holder to end the over. Length ball in the channel just outside off this time, Vihari has a poke at it but the ball shapes away to go past the hanging bat of Vihari.
Flatter on the pads, tapped towards short leg.
Flatter on middle and leg, blunts this one close to the short leg fielder.
Flatter around off, eased towards mid off this time by Pant.
FOUR! Length ball outside off, room for Pant to crunch a cut past point to earn a boundary. His first of the innings.
On middle and off, blocked by Pant.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Slightly fullish going down the leg side. Vihari paddle sweeps it fine down the leg side to get a boundary. Not a good start from Cornwall.
Fuller on the pads, worked towards deep square leg for a run.
Goes round the wicket to Pant who pushes it off his back foot.
Shortish length ball, blunted close to the short leg fielder.
Another shortish length ball, Pant blocks it with soft hands.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
Loopy fuller ball, driven towards long on for a single by Vihari.
Flatter on the pads, blocked onto the pitch.
Flatter again but outside off, leaves it alone.
Another flat ball outside off, left alone by Pant again.
Flat and full this time, pushed towards mid off.
Fuller on the stumps, blocked.
Shortish ball on middle and leg, tucked towards the leg side off his back foot.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Flatter on middle, blocked by Vihari.
Loopy  ball on middle, blocked towards mid-wicket.
Flighted around middle, blocked towards mid-wicket.
Flighted ball around off, Vihari negotiates it well.
Floated on off and middle, blocked out.
SIX! Pant comes down the track and just smashes it over the mid on fence for a biggie. First maximum of this match.
Pushed towards mid on off the back foot.
Another one on middle and off, the batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Fuller flighted ball, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter one this time, pushed towards mid off.
Shorter one around off, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Flatter around off, worked towards mid on.
Length ball on off and middle, Vihari looks to work it towards the leg side but gets a leading edge and the ball rolls towards the off side.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman.
Length ball on middle, sweeps towards deep square leg for a couple.
Fuller ball, driven wide of mid on for a single.
Another full delivery, Vihari looks to work it towards cover but gets an inside edge and the ball goes towards short leg. The batters take a single.
FOUR! Fuller ball on off, Pant leans forward to drive this past the diving cover fielder. The ball races through to the fence.
Loopy ball around off, pushed towards cover.
Flatter on middle, Pant goes back to blunt it towards the off side.
Loopy ball on off, Pant works it towards point to take a quick single.
Fuller one on middle and leg, dabbed closer to the short leg fielder.
Length ball outside off, pushed towards the off side.
FOUR BYES! Flighted fuller ball this time but it is going down the leg side. Pant goes to sweep but he misses. The keeper misses as well and the ball races to the fine leg fence.
Flighted fuller ball, pushed towards the slip cordon.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Another fast and fuller ball down the leg side, Pant goes for another sweep but misses. This time the keeper does well to stop.
Good delivery to start the new spell with the new ball. Length ball around middle and leg, Vihari looks to work it towards the leg side but he gets an inside edge on it and he is hit on the pads.
Length ball outside off, pushed back to the bowler.
Shortish ball around off, driven straight to mid on this time.
Wide outside off, Vihari lets it go.
Slightly fullish on middle and leg, Vihari looks to flick but misses and is hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards fine leg and the batters take a leg bye.
Wide outside off. Pant lets it go to the keeper.

FOUR! Poor start from Gabriel. Fuller ball outside off, Vihari leans forward and creams a cover drive for a boundary. Timed sweetly as it races to the fence. Gabriel's poor performance in the game continues.
Back of a length ball outside off, Vihari sways away from it.
Another shortish length ball outside off, left alone again by Vihari.

FOUR! Another crunching drive from Vihari. Gabriel doesn't learn as he dishes out another fuller ball outside off. Vihari reads the length early and leans into the drive to cash in on it. It races to the cover fence in a jiffy.
Shortish ball this time, blocked by staying in the crease.
Wide outside off, left alone by Vihari this time.
Length ball outside off, Pant knows where his stumps are so he lets it go to the keeper.
Gets Pant driving this time and goes past the outside edge. Fuller ball around off, Pant throws his bat at it. Lucky not to get an edge on that one.
Another length ball around off, left alone by Pant.
Goes past the outside edge this time! Length ball closer to the off pole, Pant looks to push with hard hands but the ball shapes away and goes past the outside edge. Superb bowling this from Roach.
Wide outside off this time, Pant doesn't go after it and leaves it alone.

Leading edge! Fuller ball on the pads for Pant this time. Rishabh looks to work it towards the leg side but the ball takes the leading edge and flies through the cover-point region. Hetmyer chases the ball as it races to the fence and dives to pull the ball back into play. Three runs taken.
Fuller ball around off, blocked by Pant coming forward towards cover.
Bumper down the leg side. Pant initially wanted to heave this but left it in the end.
Shortish ball on the body, blocked towards the bowler off his back foot.
Good delivery and well left fron Pant. Nicely directed back of a length ball on off and middle, Pant does well to sway away.
Another bumper, this time on the body of Pant who swivels to hammer his pull along the ground towards square leg for a single.
Bumper outside off, left alone by Vihari this time.
Length ball in the channel outside off, Pant leaves it alone.
Another one in the channel on the same line, Pant lets it be. He may not want to take any risk at this moment in time.
Too wide outside off again. Pant lets it go the keeper again.

Straighter one on the pads this time, Pant whips it nicely through square leg for three. There was no one in that direction as the mid on fielder runs towards the ball. He is too slow to return the ball towards the bowler or the keeper which allows an extra run. 50-run stand between the two. Important stand this one after the wicket of skipper Virat Kohli. Also, 250 up for India with that.

Huge appeal from Roach but nothing from the umpire. Roach dishes out a fuller ball on middle and leg as Vihari looks to flick but misses. The ball goes on to hit the pads. That looked to be going down the leg side. By the way, Roach had overstepped on that delivery but the umpire did not spot that. Also, the Ball Tracker shows that it was going down the leg side. So, the umpire gets one decision right and one wrong.
Beaten! Length ball around off, shapes away from Vihari's push and goes past the outside edge.
Length ball down the leg side. Pant goes for the flick but can't get bat on ball. The keeper pouches it down the leg side.
Fuller one on middle and leg, blocked towards mid-wicket by Pant.
Good length ball outside off, goes further away from Pant as he leaves this one alone.

Short one on the body of Pant. He swivels to hammer this towards mid-wicket. Pant hared for the third run as the ball went towards the fence. The fielder stops the ball and throws the ball back to the keeper who breaks the bails but Vihari was well in.
Shortish one on the body, tucked towards the leg side for a run.
Fuller ball outside off, Pant strokes it straight to mid off.
Last over of the day. Roach steams in and bowls a good length ball outside off, pushed back towards the bowler by Vihari.
Length ball wide outside off, Vihari shoulders arms to it.
Fullish one wide outside off, Vihari looks to push this towards the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR! On the pads of Vihari, he clips this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary. Great shot this!
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Vihari.
FOUR! Last ball of the day, and Vihari ends it with a boundary! This one is also full and on the pads, he flicks it wide of mid-wicket and the ball trudges towards the fence. STUMPS ON DAY 1.

OUT! BOWLED! Brilliant start from the hosts as Pant has been bowled over. Holder steams in and rocks Pant over on the first ball of the day. He bowls this one on a length just outside off and shapes back in after pitching. Pant goes for a push off the first ball of the day but misses the line and the ball crashes into middle and off. Rash by Pant this and Holder is delighted. Four wickets for him in this innings so far.
FOUR! Down the leg side and Jadeja just flicks it fine towards fine leg for the first boundary of the day. Jadeja gets off the mark here with this boundary.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Way wide outside off, Jadeja leaves this one alone as Hamilton dives to his left and collects it.
Fuller one this time, Jadeja pushes it out.
Down the leg side again by Holder, Jadeja leaves it alone. An eventful first over of the day comes to an end. A wicket and four runs from it.
First ball of the day for Roach, length ball outside off, left alone by Vihari.
Another length ball by Roach, Vihari is patient enough to not fiddle with it.
This time Vihari does play at it. Fullish ball outside off, Vihari pushes it in the gap at cover and takes a couple.
Good length ball just outside off, coming back in towards Vihari. He does well to keep it down and dabs it towards the leg side.
Outside off, Vihari shoulders arms to this one.
Beaten! Vihari goes to defend this length ball off his back foot but does so inside the line and is beaten by the away movement. The hosts are piling up the pressure.
On a length on off, Jadeja blocks it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on middle, Jadeja blocks it towards the point fielder.
Another good ball from Holder. It is bowled on a length around off, Jadeja sees the ball go through the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle, swinging into the batsman, Ravindra looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pad.
Full delivery on middle, Jadeja attempts to drive it hard but gets an inside edge into the pads. No harm done though.
Good length ball on middle, Jadeja looks to flick but again gets hit high on the pads. The ball rolls to point. Another excellent over from the Windies skipper.
Good length ball around off, Vihari pushes it wide of mid on and takes one.
FOUR! Short of a length ball outside off, Jadeja opens the face of his bat and guides it towards the third man fence.
Outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to this one.
Another one outside off, left alone.
Beaten! Terrific ball by Roach. Length ball around the fourth stump line, it pitches and straightens. The ball whizzes past the outside edge of Jadeja's bat.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Bouncer to Vihari this time, he ducks under this one and lets it through to Hamilton.
Good length ball on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.

Beaten! Holder getting some great movement off the surface here. This pitches on a good length outside off. It swings away from the batter as Vihari looks to play at it. He is beaten all ends up by this one.
Risky leave! Length ball outside off, this time the ball keeps its trajectory but rises on him. Vihari tries to leave but the ball hits the toe end of his bat and falls short of the keeper.
Outside off, Vihari chooses to leave this one alone.
Fullish outside off, pushed to the man at cover.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja lets it go through to the keeper.
Fuller this time outside off, pushed towards cover.
Outside off again, Jadeja patiently leaves it alone again. Doesn't look in any hurry.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja gets onto the back foot and pushes this towards point.
Another length ball, again Jadeja looks to defend it but he gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Bouncer on the first ball of the over by Holder. Vihari ducks under it.
Full on the pads of Vihari, he tucks it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Another bouncer by Holder, this time to Jadeja on the leg pole line. He ducks under it.
Excellent length by Holder here. This has pitched on a good length here on middle, it straightens and hits Jadeja on the box as he misses his flick. He looks to be in some pain here.

This is again wide outside off and left alone by Jadeja. Hamilton has a shy at the keeper's end and hits but Jadeja is well in. The ball deflects off the timber towards the leg side and a run is taken.

FOUR! Fifty for Vihari although in fortunate fashion. Holder bowls this on a length just outside off, Vihari tries to push it towards point but gets an inside edge on it. He almost chops it onto the stumps but he is fortunate as it misses the timber and goes towards the fine leg fence. Third half ton for Vihari and he will be looking to convert this into his first ton.
Good length ball on off, Jadeja defends it off the back foot.
On a length on off, Jadeja blocks it out.
Good length ball around off, Ravindra defends it to point.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

Fullish on middle and leg, Vihari blocks it out towards mid on and takes a quick single. The fielder there takes a shy at the bowler's end and hits but it looks like Vihari is well in. The umpire takes it upstairs for the confirmation. The replays roll in and yes, HV is indeed well in.
Length ball outside off, Jadeja pushes this off the back foot towards point.

FOUR! Off the shoulder of Jadeja's bat. Holder bowls this one on a good length around off, Jadeja looks to tap it onto the pitch but the ball hits the shoulder of Jadeja's bat. It flies over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
Length ball around middle and off, Jadeja defends it off the back foot.
FOUR! Shortish delivery around off, Vihari guides it to gully where the ball goes through the fielder for a boundary. It seems that the bounce was awkward for the fielder there.
Back of a length delivery, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari plays this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls a bouncer on the leg stump line, Hanuma ducks under it.
Shortish in length ball down the leg side, Vihari leaves it alone.
Outside off by Cornwall to start off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Short again outside off, Jadeja cuts it off the back foot past point where the fielder misfields and the batters take a couple.
Tossed up just outside off, pushed out towards mid off.
Another one, tossed up outside off, Jadeja blocks it out.
Jadeja defends this fuller one by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Tossed up outside off, blocked again by Jadeja towards the off side.
Good length ball on the off pole, Vihari blocks it off the back foot towards mid on.
On the hips of Vihari this time, he flicks it towards backward square leg and rotates the strike.
Short of a length outside off, Jadeja does not fiddle with it and lets it through to Hamilton.
Another short of a length ball, this time on the leg side. Jadeja looks to keep it down but is hit on the gloves. It goes uppishly towards short leg but falls well short.
Bumper outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Good running by Jadeja. Another shorter one on the off side, Jadeja just taps it down towards the off side and takes a quick single.
Tossed up outside off, blocked out by RJ.
Similar one by Cornwall, Jadeja again blocks it out.
Shorter one this time, Jadeja cuts it towards point.
Floated outside off, Jadeja pushes this back towards the bowler.
Tossed up on the pads this time, Jadeja flicks it towards the leg side.
Again on the pads, Jadeja defends it back towards Cornwall. Maiden over by him.

This shows just how sure Vihari is where his wickets are. This is a length ball coming into Vihari, he shuffles across and shoulders arms to it. It was close to the stumps as the ball went past him but he was never in doubt.
Length ball on middle and leg, it hits the pads of Vihari and goes towards square leg as they take one.
Outside off, length ball. Left alone by RJ.
Good fielding by John Campbell. Jadeja plays this length ball off the back foot towards point where Campbell dives to his right and saves at least a couple for the hosts.
Another length ball outside off, Jadeja does not fiddle at it.
Outside off again, Jadeja tries to put bat on ball on this one but misses it altogether due to the movement on it.
On the pads to start off after drinks by Cornwall, Vihari pushes this towards mid-wicket.

Top edged but safe! This time Cornwall tosses it up outside off, Vihari goes down on one knee and tries to sweep. He gets a top edge on it and the ball skies towards the short fine leg region. The fielder hares after it but cannot get to it as the batters take one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Another one tossed up around off, Jadeja pushes it out.
Short this time outside off, pushed towards the man at point.
Short again around middle and off, Jadeja blocks it off the back foot.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Vihari.
Length ball around middle and off, Vihari blocks this off the back foot towards the off side.
Another length ball outside off, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Outside off, left alone.
Great shot by Vihari. Length ball outside off, Vihari hops and crunches this one through covers off the back foot. It does not have the power in it to reach the fence and the batters take three.
Tossed up outside off, pushed out by Vihari.
Another one floated outside off, Vihari defends it out.
Shortish this time by Cornwall, Vihari flicks this towards fine leg and takes a couple. 300 up for India with this couple.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Vihari looks to block this one off the front foot but the ball hits the knee roll and goes towards short leg.
Vihari punches this one straight down the ground. Cornwall sticks his hand out and catches it with his right hand.
Played through mid-wicket by Vihari.
Outside off, left alone by RJ.
Length ball on middle and off, Jadeja defends this one out off the back foot.
Jadeja leaves this one outside off and the ball goes through to Hamilton.
Another length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja pushes it out.
Length ball on middle and leg again, pushed towards the man at mid on off the back foot.
This time off the back foot towards mid off by Jadeja. He is playing very well here.
Loopy ball on middle, pushed towards short leg.
Another one floated on middle and leg, Vihari pushes it towards the leg side.
HV gets on top of the bounce and flicks it towards the leg side.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Another one full and floated on off, pushed towards mid-wicket by Hanuma.
Similar ball, similar result. Tossed up on leg and pushed to mid-wicket by Vihari. Another maiden over by Cornwall.
Length ball around the fifth stump line, Jadeja leaves it alone.
This one is way outside off, carries to Hamilton behind the wickets at a comfortable height. The moisture seems to have disappeared a bit and the surface seems to be a bit harder than yesterday too.
Beaten! Beauty by Roach. In the corridor of uncertainty, on a length. The ball pitches and moves away from Jadeja as he tries to fend at it. It goes past his outside edge by a whisker.

Quick and smart running by Jadeja. Roach bowls this one fuller and on off, Jadeja pushes this towards Gabriel at mid on. He sets off immediately knowing that Gabriel will not be quick enough to run him out. If there was anyone else over there, this could have been close.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Vihari plays that one off the front foot and onto the ground.

OUT! CAUGHT! Jadeja throws his wicket away after being patient for a long time. It is a flighted delivery on middle, Jadeja goes for the slog sweep over mid-wicket but gets a top edge on it which goes way up in the air. Darren Bravo at mid on positions himself under it and takes a simple catch. It was looking like Jadeja was itching to go for the big shot here and in doing so, he perishes. Cornwall provides the crucial breakthrough for the hosts.
Looped up ball on middle, Vihari flicks it to mid-wicket.
Shorter delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Tossed up on off pole, Ishant pushes it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Sharma defends this off the front foot and onto the ground. End of a successful over for the West Indies.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery  way outside off, Vihari leaves it alone. It has been wided.
On a length outside off, Vihari lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari drives this nicely to mid on and takes a single.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Ishant blocks it off the back foot
Good length delivery around off, Sharma leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Ishant lets it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Tossed up ball outside off, Vihari paddles this one nicely towards the fine leg fence for a boundary. Much needed runs for the Men In Blue.
Tossed up ball around off, Vihari blocks it out.

DROPPED! John Campbell is the man again just like the first Test match. Vihari looks to lunge forward and defend this ball on the off side. He gets a thick outside edge on it and the ball goes wide to the right of first slip where John Campbell is positioned. He dives in an attempt to catch it. He gets his right hand on it but is unable to hold onto it. Hanuma survives and he will now be looking to make the most of it.
FOUR! Punished by Vihari immediately. On the pads this time by Cornwall and Vihari pounces it as he flicks this one towards mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short outside off, cut to point by Vihari.

FOUR! Great shot by Vihari and he is looking to go on the offensive here. Short again this time, Vihari rocks onto the back foot and slams it through mid-wicket for another boundary. 12 off the over and a dropped catch!

FOUR OVERTHROWS! What was Ishant and Vihari doing here? Ishant defends this good length ball towards the off side and is called by Vihari for a run here. Brathwaite comes to the ball quickly and has a shy at the stumps. He misses and the ball races to the long on fence for a boundary. Bonus runs for India here. 5 runs for India here. Had the fielder hit, Ishant would have been out as he was well out. He survives to fight another Day.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari plays it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Ishant defends it to point.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Bowls a full delivery this time on the legs, Ishant who had moved towards the off side looks to flick but misses.
BEATEN! Excellent over from Holder comes to an end. Coming to this ball, it is bowled on a length around off, Ishant looks to defend but misses it completely.
Flatter one on middle and leg, pushed towards square leg by Vihari and he takes a single.
FOUR! Aggresive from Ishant. Tossed up on middle and off, Ishant slog sweeps it over square leg for a boundary. Unusual from Ishant this.
On the pads of Ishant, this time he flicks it off his pads towards square leg and takes a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Another one short and on off, Vihari flicks this one towards backward square leg and takes one.
Another fuller one, blocked out by Sharma onto the ground.
Beaten! Holder bowls a peach of a delivery! Vihari looks to defend this one but misses as he does so down the wrong line.

NOT OUT! Missing the leg pole and Vihari survives. Holder bowls a length ball outside off and it is coming back into Vihari. He misses his flick to get hit on the pad. The Windies players appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Vihari has a chat with Ishant and goes for the review. The replays roll in. Ultra Edge shows no edge on that one. Ball Tracker comes in, pitching outside off, impact in line, but GOING OVER THE LEG POLE. Successful review for India and their two reviews remain intact. Vihari is still at the crease although riding his luck a bit.
Vihari drives this through the covers. The batters have run through for a single.
Sharma defends it from within the crease towards mid off.
Down the leg side, Sharma knows exactly where his stumps are and leaves it alone.
On middle and off, Sharma blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Vihari defends it to the leg side.
Looped up ball on middle, Vihari pushes this to long on and takes a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Ishant tries to flick it but it hits the pads and it goes towards the short fine leg fielder.
The batsman plays a sweep shot. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Shorter in length this time on middle, Ishant defends it back to the bowler.
Outside off by Holder, Hanuma leaves this one alone.

Oh dear. Direct hit and Ishant was gone for all money. He was literally sold a dummy down the river there and had no way to go. But now, to add salt to the wound, the batsmen take an overthrow as well. It was a length ball just outside off, Vihari pushed this towards cover-point and set off for a single. Now, one cannot blame Ishant for not responding at all. He is a fast bowler and would have looked at the clock and probably thought, Lunch is around the corner. Suddenly, he is called for a quick single. Now, he is in no position to respond and starts scurrying towards the keeper's end. He knows he is gone and gives up pretty early when he sees Kraigg Brathwaite pick up the ball. The former skipper takes an aim and has a shy at the stumps at the striker's end, but on the run. That causes some imbalance and he misses it, with Sharma heaving a sigh of relief. The ball goes towards deep backward square leg and in the meantime, Vihari calls his partner for another run.
Vihari shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Vihari goes after this wide one but misses his slash at it.
Length ball just outside off, pushed towards mid on by Vihari.
Outside off again Vihari lets it go. LUNCH ON DAY 2!
Starts with a short delivery on middle, Sharma blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on middle, Sharma sweeps this nicely towards square leg and takes a single.
Short delivery on off, Vihari plays it to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg.
BEATEN! Short delivery on off, Vihari looks to defend but gets beaten. The ball stayed low after pitching and Vihari is beaten as a result.
Flighted delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on off, Ishant drives this nicely towards cover for a couple.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Another full one on the pads, Vihari flicks it to fine leg and takes a single. The fielder misfields but no extras taken.
A bumper on off, Ishant leaves it alone.
Short ball on off, Sharma rocks back and pulls it to square leg and takes a single.
Short delivery on off, Vihari guides it to point.
Full delivery on the leg stump line, Ishant flicks it to mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played from Ishant here. It is a good length delivery on middle, Ishant flicks this towards fine leg for a boundary. Second boundary for him here.
On a length on middle, Ishant blocks it to mid-wicket.
Good length delivery outside off, Ishant lets it go.
Good length delivery on off, Sharma blocks it off the back foot.
Another good length delivery around off, Ishant blocks it towards the point region.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari flicks this to fine leg and takes a single.
Full delivery on off, Ishant flicks this towards the square leg region and takes a single. John Campbell runs in from fine leg and makes a good stop.
A bumper from Gabriel to which Vihari ducks under.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Hanuma looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg.
Back of a length delivery on off, Hanuma defends this off the back foot.

FOUR! Brilliantly played from Ishant. It is a full delivery around off, Ishant plays a lovely drive towards the cover region for a boundary. This is probably the best shot that Ishant has played in this innings so far. With this the 50-run stand is up between the two. 350 also comes up for India.
Holder, coming around the wicket, bowls a bumper over the head of the batsman, Ishant ducks under it.
BEATEN! Good ball from Holder. It is a good length delivery around off, Ishant looks to defend but fails to put bat on it.
Back of a length delivery on off, Ishant guides it to point.
EDGED AND FOUR! Frustrating for the hosts here. Holder bowls a full delivery around off, Ishant looks to drive but gets a thick outside edge which goes through the gully region for a boundary.
Fuller delivery on middle, Sharma flicks this nicely towards mid-wicket and takes a couple. Good over for India as 10 runs came off it.
On a length outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Good ball from Gabriel. Bowls a full delivery around the fourth stump line, Vihari goes for a tentative drive but misses the ball completely.
Good length delivery way outside the off stump line, Vihari does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Viahri shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Hanuma attempts to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg. Good bowling this from Gabriel.
Outswinging delivery outside off, Vihari first looks to drive but pulls out at the last moment and lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Ishant pushes this to mid off.
Back of a length delivery around off, Sharma leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on off, Ishant defends this one back to the bowler.
On a length outside the off pole line, Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Short delivery on off, Sharma defends this nicely off the back foot.
Good length delivery outside off, Ishant leaves it alone.
On a length outside off swinging away from the batsman, Vihari leaves it alone.
Full delivery around off, Vihari drives this towards mid off.
Good length delivery around the fourth stump line, Vihari defends this to the off side.

OHH! Bowls an inswinger this time does Gabriel. All the balls before this were outswingers. Vihari fails to read it and leaves this alone.  It is a brilliant set up here from Gabriel who almost broke this stand with this ball.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Vihari plays it to mid on.
Good length delivery on the leg stump line, Vihari tries to flick it but misses.
Fullish delivery on off, Ishant looks to flick but gets an outside edge towards cover for a single.
LEG BYE! It is a good length ball on leg, Vihari looks to flick but gets hit on the pads and the ball rolls to fine leg. They take a single.
Back of a length delivery on off, Ishant defends this off the back foot.
Full delivery on off, Sharma pushes this towards mid off.
Full delivery on middle, IS blocks it out.
Good length delivery around off, Ishant leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Vihari pushes this towards mid on.
Good length delivery just outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Vihari pushes this to mid on.
On a length on middle, Hanuma defends it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Poor ball from Gabriel. Gabriel bowls this full delivery on the pads of Vihari and he obliges as he plays a lovely flick towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. A boundary after a long time for him. He moves into the 90s here.
Good length delivery on off, Vihari defends it off the front foot.
Good length ball around off, Ishant pushes this to point.
Full delivery on the fourth stump line, Sharma drives this towards point.
Bowls a good length delivery around off, Ishant attempts to defend this but gets an edge towards second slip where the fielder collects it on a bounce.
Back of a length delivery on off, Ishant guides this towards the third man region and takes a couple.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Sharma shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma flicks this nicely towards the mid-wicket region and takes a couple. The partnership moves to 66 runs.
Short delivery on off, Vihari pushes this to long on and takes a single.
Flighted delivery on off, Sharma blocks it out.

FOUR! Sharma is batting like a proper batsman here. It is a loopy delivery on off, Ishant sweeps this nicely towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. Excellent batting this from Ishant, moves into the 40s with this.

FOUR LEG BYES! Roston bowls a flighted delivery outside leg, Ishant looks to sweep but misses. The ball goes through the keeper's gloves and into the fine leg fence. The keeper must have been blinded by Sharma's bat here.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Ishant attempts to defend but fails to put bat on it. Good comeback from Chase.
Looped up ball on middle, Ishant flicks this nicely towards fine leg and before the fielder cleans up, the batters take a couple.
Good length ball outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Back of a length delivery on off, Vihari pushes this to point where Chase is sloppy in cleaning it up. The ball goes through and allows the batsman to take a single.
Good length ball around off, Ishant in an attempt to defend it gets an edge towards second slip and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Vihari blocks this back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Vihari defends it off the back foot.
LEG BYE! Chase bowls a full delivery on off, Ishant looks to sweep but misses and gets hit on the pads. The ball goes past short leg. The batters take a single.
Flighted delivery outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
FOUR! Good shot from Vihari. It is a short delivery outside off, Vihari rocks back and slaps it through the cover region for a boundary. Moves to 96 with that boundary.
Another short ball around off, Vihari guides this towards the third man region for a couple. Vihari is just two away from his first Test century.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket.
Looped up delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg and takes a single. With that, Hanuma moves to 99. Good over for India here as eight runs came off it.

Maiden Test hundred for Vihari and he breathes a huge sigh of relief. Whole of the Indian dressing room stands up and applauds him. Full and on the pads of Vihari, he flicks it towards mid-wicket and sets off for the single. The fielder there has a shy at the keeper's end but misses. Ishant was well in anyway and even if that had hit, it wouldn't have made a difference. Vihari takes off his helmet and celebrates with his bat held up high. A huge moment for any cricketer to get to his first Test hundred.
FOUR! Sharma gets in on the act as he lifts this short delivery outside off over the slip cordon and into the third man fence for a boundary.
Good length delivery on middle, Sharma blocks this back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Sharma pushes this to mid-wicket. Vihari wanted a single there and is sent back by Ishant. The fielder has a shy at the stumps but misses.
Good length ball outside off, Ishant looks to defend but gets an edge towards third man and takes a single.
Yorker aimed at the middle, Ishant manages to keep it out.
