Flighted delivery on middle, Vihari defends it to short leg.
BEATEN! Vihari attempts to defend but fails to put any bat on it.
Short delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg.
Looped up ball on middle, Vihari blocks it out back to the bowler.
On middle, defended back to the bowler by Vihari.
Flighted delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Good length ball around off, Vihari pushes it out.
FOUR! Full and just outside off, Vihari leans into the drive and pushes this through mid off for a boundary. 400 up for India.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Vihari pushes this to cover.
On a length outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari pushes this to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Vihari blocks it out.

FIFTY FOR ISHANT! First one for him in Test cricket. Cornwall bowls a full delivery on middle, Ishant sweeps this towards square leg and takes a single. Excellent innings from Ishant. Who would think that Ishant is a bowler. With this 100- run stand is also up.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flighted delivery on middle, Vihari plays this towards mid on and takes a single.
Looped up ball on off, Sharma defends this off the front foot.

DROPPED! Cornwall drops it off his own bowling. Bowls a loopy delivery on middle, Ishant comes down the track and plays this drive uppishly and  hard but straight towards the bowler. Cornwall attempts to catch it but is unable to hold onto it. A single is taken in the meantime.
Loopy delivery on middle, Vihari blocks it out.
Ishant comes down the track and tries to heave this over mid-wicket. It takes the outside half of Ishant's bat and the ball goes to long off for one.
On the pads of Vihari, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
FOUR! A great paddle shot time on this ball down the leg side and the ball races to the fine leg fence.

Sharma comes down the track and goes for another heave towards the leg side. He misses this time to get hit on the pads. It deflects off it and goes between the keeper Hamilton and first slip towards the third man fence as the batters take one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Down the leg side by Kraigg, Vihari goes for the paddle this time but he misses.
Full delivery on off, Sharma sweeps this to fine leg. No run.
Short ball on off, Ishant flicks this to fine leg.
Flighted delivery on middle, Ishant comes down the track and gets a top edge towards square leg. The fielder takes it on the bounce.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads.
Loopy delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Bowls a loopy delivery on off, Ishant expands his horizon and tries to reverse sweep it but misses.
Flighted delivery on the leg stump line, Vihari looks to flick but misses.
Looped up ball on off, Vihari flicks it towards the leg side and takes a single.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ishant Sharma's brilliant innings comes to an end. Sharma comes down the track to this loopy delivery and tries to slog it away for a maximum but does not time it well. He gets a top edge towards deep mid-wicket where Hetmyer takes a simple catch. A magnificent 112-run partnership is over and it has led India to a commanding position. West Indies will be looking to bundle out the visitors quickly now.
Short delivery on middle, Vihari punches this off the back foot towards the off side and takes a single.
Short ball on middle, Shami flicks it towards fine leg.
Good length ball on off, Vihari shuffles and tucks it towards square leg to take a single.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Third wicket for the debutant Cornwall here. It is a short delivery outside off, Shami looks to cut but gets a thick outside edge straight to the keeper Hamilton who takes an easy catch. The ball bounces a little bit more and Shami fails to cope up with it. Very little celebration from the Windies here.
Flighted delivery on middle, Bumrah blocks it out.
Looped ball on middle, Bumrah defends this one.
Loopy delivery on middle, Bumrah plays it to short leg.
BEATEN! Excellent over from Cornwall. It is a flighted delivery around off, Bumrah looks to defend but misses the ball completely.

OUT! CAUGHT! Sixth five-fer for the West Indies skipper which also brings up 100 Test scalps for him. Vihari is the last man to be dismissed. Holder bowls this one full and just outside off, Vihari looks to clear the mid on fielder but gets a thick outside edge on it. The ball goes high in the air towards mid off where Kemar Roach runs back, settles himself under it and takes a good catch. India finish their first innings on 416 and have set a stiff total in front of the hosts.
Length ball outside off to start by Ishant. Brathwaite pushes it towards cover.
Another length ball but this is way outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Fuller this time by Ishant, pushed to mid on off the front foot.
Outside off by Ishant, Kraigg leaves it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Brathwaite.

Good bowling by Ishant, brings the last delivery of the over into the batter and he was almost beaten. Good length ball outside off, it shapes back in towards Kraigg. He manages to get bat on it at the last moment and the ball goes to fine leg as the batters take one. West Indies are underway with that single.
Length ball by Bumrah, he brings it back into the batter. Kraigg shoulders arms to it but that was too close for comfort.
Outside off by Bumrah, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Good length ball shaping into Kraigg, he defends it out off his front foot.
Outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Beaten! Beauty by Jasprit. Good length ball just outside off, the ball pitches and swings away. Brathwaite tries to fend at it but misses as he does so inside the line.
Fuller ball around off stump. Blocked off the outside half of the bat by Kraigg.
Length ball on the middle pole line, Campbell looks to play at it but misses to get hit on the thigh pad.
Length ball outside off, Campbell leaves it alone.
Another ball outside off, left alone by Campbell.
Fuller this time on middle and off, pushed back down the ground by John.
Another good length ball around off, Campbell again blocks this one out.
Fuller around middle and off, Campbell pushes it past the bowler towards mid on.
Bouncer by Bumrah. Brathwaite does well as he sways away from it.
Good length ball pitching outside off, it shapes back in sharply. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it but this once again goes past the stumps missing by a whisker.
On middle and leg, Kraigg pushes this towards short leg with soft hands.
Outside off, similar to the ball before the last one. Brathwaite shoulders arms to it.
Outside off again coming back in, Brathwaite moves towards it and then shoulders arms at the last moment.
Fuller one on the off side, Brathwaite pushes this towards mid off. Bumrah is lazy in getting down and the ball goes past Shami from extra cover. Two runs taken.
Full one outside off, Campbell pushes this towards cover.
Length ball outside off, Campbell does not fiddle with it.
Length ball outside off, the ball swings into the batter and John shoulders arms to it.
Another one outside off, left alone by the batter.
Short of a length outside off, Campbell gets up on his toes and pulls this towards square leg. He takes a couple and gets off the mark.
FOUR LEG BYES! On the pads this time by Sharma, Campbell looks to flick this one but misses. The ball hits the thigh pad and it goes into the fine leg fence.
Length ball on middle and off, Brathwaite defends it out off the back foot.
Kraigg leaves this length ball outside off.
Good length ball around off, it pitches and moves away. Brathwaite looks to put bat on ball on this one but misses.
Another one outside off, Brathwaite leaves it alone.
Length ball way outside off, left alone by Brathwaite.
Down the leg side this time, Brathwaite lets it go to the keeper. Maiden over to start off for Shami.
Corker of a yorker by Bumrah but John survives this time. Bumrah comes over the wicket and bowls this on the off pole. Campbell does well to jam it out.
Full ball around off, Campbell looks to drive this one but is beaten by the away movement.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pant takes the catch and the first wicket of the Windies is down. Length ball pitching just outside leg, the ball goes away from Campbell with the angle. John tries to fend at it but does so inside the line. It takes the faintest of outside edges of Campbell's bat and goes towards the left of Pant who takes the catch. The hosts trail by 407 with 9 wickets in hand.
On the pads of Bravo, he tucks it towards fine leg and takes a single to get off the mark.
Outside off, left alone by Kraigg.
Outside off, Darren Bravo leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle and off, Bravo pushes this past short leg and takes a couple.
Fullish one just outside off, Bravo looks to tuck it towards the leg side but gets a leading edge on it and the ball goes towards covers.

Good length ball on middle and leg. Bravo looks to flick this one but misses to get hit on the thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal by the Indian players but nothing from the umpire. Looks to be going down leg.
On the pads again, this time Bravo flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Outside off, left alone by Darren.

OUT! CAUGHT! Another southpaw bites the dust against Bumrah. Length ball again on middle and leg, it pitches and moves away from Bravo. He tries to drive at it but gets a thick outside edge on it. It flies to second slip where KL Rahul is stationed and he takes the catch. The hosts are looking in trouble here.

OUT! LBW! Brooks is out on a golden duck and Bumrah is on a hat-trick. This one is fullish and around off, coming into Brooks. He looks to drive at this one but misses it completely as he plays down the wrong line. The Indian players appeal and up goes the umpire's finger. Brooks goes for the review after consulting with his partner. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows no bat on that. Ball Tracker comes into play and shows three reds and Brooks has to take the long walk back. West Indies lose their first review.

OUT! LBW! Bumrah has taken a hat-trick here and the hosts are in complete shambles. Bumrah is the man who is ripping them apart. This is a full ball around off coming in towards Chase. He looks to flick but misses to get hit on the front pad. The Indian players appeal but the umpire denies it. Bumrah thinks that there is some bat on that one but Virat is convinced that this hit the pad first. He goes for the review after having a good chat with Bumrah. Ultra Edge comes in and confirms that the Indian skipper is right, there is no edge on that. Ball Tracker comes in, pitching outside off, impact in line and HITTING THE WICKETS! Successful review for India and India are on a roll here. Jasprit Bumrah becomes the third Indian to take a Test hat-trick. The hosts trail by 403 and they are already 4 wickets down.
Way wide outside off, Hetmyer gets an edge on this one and this goes towards third alip all along the ground and the batters take one.
Brathwaite shoulders arms to let that one through. Bumrah has shattered the West Indies batting line up in this over.

Good length delivery on off, Hetmyer defends it off the front foot. Hetmyer looks to run first and Brathwaite obliges. Kraigg is sent back by Hetmyer at the last moment. The fielder at cover has a shy at the stumps but misses. Brathwaite was well out.
Good length outside off, Hetmyer leaves it alone.
Yorker on middle, Hetmyer manages to block this one towards the leg side.
Back of a length delivery around off, Shimron shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Good ball from Shami. It is a good length delivery outside off, Shimron looks to defend but ends up missing the ball completely.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Hetmyer defends it off the back foot. Good over from Shami.
Good length ball on middle, Kraigg flicks it to mid on and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off swinging into the batsman, Shimron leaves it alone. The ball passed very close to the off stump yet again.
Full delivery on off, Hetmyer drives this towards mid off.
Length ball around middle and leg, it nips back in after pitching. It goes off the thigh pad towards Rishabh Pant as Hetmyer misses his push towards mid on.
Yorker around middle and off, Hetmyer jams this one out back towards Bumrah.
Another yorker, this time Shimron jams it out towards mid off.
Length ball around middle and off, Brathwaite blocks it out off the back foot.
Length ball around off again, Brathwaite shoulders arms to it at the last moment.
Jaffa! What a delivery by Shami! He bowls this on the fourth stump line, and gets it to nip away. Brathwaite tries to defend but does so inside the line and is beaten by the movement.
On the pads of Brathwaite, he flicks it towards square leg and takes a couple.
Another superb delivery by Shami. Length ball again to Brathwaite, he tries to defend it but in the end takes his bat away from the line of the delivery.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Top edged but safe! Bouncer by Bumrah to Hetmyer, he looks to hook but gets a top edge on it. The ball uppishly goes towards fine leg for a single.
Length ball outside off, Brathwaite tries to put bat on ball on this but is beaten.

India appeal loudly for a caught behind but nothing from the umpire. Length ball just outside off, it straightens after pitching. Brathwaite looks to block this one but does so inside the line as the ball goes past the bat and it misses by a whisker. The Indian players appeal loudly as they think he has edged that. The Indians think about the review but decide against it. Replays roll in and Ultra Edge confirms the umpire's decision as there is no spike on it.
FOUR! Fullish and outside, Brathwaite pushes this one through the cover region and into the fence. A rare loose ball by Bumrah.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bumrah gets his fifth five-fer and he is in a class of his own right now. This one is on a good length just around off, Bumrah gets it to swing away off the surface just a tad bit. Brathwaite goes for another cover drive and is sucked into this one again. He gets a thick outside edge on this one and it goes low towards the right of  Pant who dives and takes a good catch. India are completely on top of the hosts here and right now this seems to be heading towards the follow-on scenario.
Down the leg side by Bumrah, Holder tries to flick but misses it.
Full delivery on off, Hetmyer pushes this to mid-wicket.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery from Shami. It is bowled on a length outside off, Hetmyer attempts for an expansive drive but fails to put bat on it.

DROPPED! The Indian captain is the culprit here! Hetmyer was dropped from Kohli in the last match as well but did not make full use of it. Will he make full use of it this time? Coming to the ball, it was a good length delivery outside off, Hetmyer attempts to drive but gets an edge towards Kohli at third slip where he makes a complete mess of it. The batters take a run.
Guided down to fine leg by the batsman. One run added to the total.

OHH! Shami bowls a good length ball outside off, Hetmyer leaves this one alone. Pant does not collect it cleanly as he dives to his right. The ball goes behind the keeper and the batsmen take off for a run. Pujara runs from first slip and throws the ball towards the keeper's end. It hits the top of the stumps and the ball goes towards extra cover.
Good length ball on off, Hetmyer drives this towards mid on.
Full toss on the pads of Holder, he flicks it towards backward square leg for a couple as the fielder in the deep sweeps it up.
Way wide outside off, this is left alone by Holder.
Length ball outside off, Holder shoulders arms to it.

Length ball around off again, it drifts into the batter here. Holder looks to block it out but misses it. The ball hits Holder on the pads and the Indian players appeal loudly. The umpire shakes his head. The Indian players ponder over taking a review but ultimately decide against taking it.
Length delivery just outside off, Holder looks to defend it off the back foot but does so inside the line of the delivery and is beaten.
Peach of a delivery yet again by Sharma. Again on a length just outside off and it nips away, Holder looks to defend it but is beaten again.
Floated around middle and off, blocked out by Hetmyer.
Another one floated on off, blocked out by Shimron.
FOUR! First shot of aggression from Hetmyer here. It is a flighted delivery on off, Hetmyer lofts this over the mid-wicket fielder for a boundary.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.

FOUR! Hetmyer is looking to attack the spinner here. It is a length delivery on off, Shimron comes down the track and plays a lofted drive just past the mid off fielder for the second boundary of the over.
Looped up ball on off, Hetmyer flicks it to fine leg and takes a single.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Hetmyer.
Drifting into Hetmyer, this good length ball. Shimron defends it towards mid on.
Beaten! The bowler is Ishant again but the batter this time is Hetmyer. Another length ball outside off, it pitches and straightens.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
On the off side this time by Sharma, Hetmyer leaves it alone.
Fullish ball just outside off, Hetmyer pushes it back towards the bowler
Flatter just outside off, it pitches and straightens. Holder looks to play at it first but decides to leave the ball alone.
Another shortish one around off, pushed towards mid off, off the back foot.
Floated and full around off, pushed out by Holder.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

FOUR BYES! Beauty by Jadeja! It pitches on the off pole line and turns away sharply from Holder. He tries to defend it off the front foot but the turn does him in. Rishabh Pant also lets this one through his gloves and the ball goes to the third man fence. Some Indian players thought there was an edge on it but the umpire's signal confirms that there isn't one. Hang on. Replays show that Holder had dragged his feet out of his crease. Which means, a STUMPING CHANCE MISSED.
Full and floated on the off pole, pushed towards the man at cover.
Good length ball on off, Hetmyer blocks it out off the back foot.

FOUR! Good shot from Hetmyer. It is a good length delivery outside off, Hetmyer rocks back and drives this past the cover fielder where Mayank runs after it and tries to make a a diving stop. Agarwal touches the fence while pushing the ball back inside the ropes. It is given a boundary in the end.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, left alone by Hetmyer.
Length ball outside off this time, Hetmyer pushes it towards cover off the back foot and takes one.
Length ball outside off this time, blocked out.
Full and floated on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Another one darted into the pads, flicked towards mid-wicket.
Full and floated on off, pushed back by Shimron.
This is floated outside off and the ball turns in sharply towards the leg side. Hetmyer tucks it towards the leg side and takes a single.
This one is pitched on middle and off, it spins away from Holder and beats the outside edge of his blade.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Fuller and on middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket.

DROPPED! EDGED AND FOUR! Another one fuller and outside off, there is some outward movement on this. Hetmyer goes for the drive but he gets a thick outside edge on it. It flies wide towards second slip where Rahul dives to his left and gets one hand on it. However, he fails to hang onto it. Had he taken that, it would have been a blinder. Hetmyer survives again.

EDGED AND FOUR! Hetmyer is living dangerously over here. It is a good length all outside off, Hetmyer attempts to drive but gets a thick outside edge and the ball goes over the second slip fielder for another boundary.
Good length ball around off, Hetmyer blocks it off the back foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! It seems here that Hetmyer will get boundaries from edges only. Bowls a good delivery outside off, Hetmyer goes for an expansive drive but only gets an outside edge past the third slip and gully fielder for the third boundary of the over.
Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer leaves it alone.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Shorter this time outside off, it turns away sharply. Holder slashes at it but misses.
Floated fuller this time, Holder defends it off the front foot.
Another one floated outside off, Holder taps it onto the ground.
Shortish ball outside off, Holder rocks onto the back foot and cuts it past point for a couple. The fielder in the deep does well to mop it up.

EDGED AND FOUR! The hosts are riding their luck here. Jadeja bowls this one full again and gets it to turn, Holder looks to block it but gets a thick outside edge on it as the ball goes towards the third man fence.
Fuller on middle and leg, pushed towards mid on.
Length ball outside off, left alone by the batter.
Another fuller one outside off, driven towards the man at mid off.
Outside off, length ball, left alone by Hetmyer.
The batsman has attempted to put bat on ball but fails.
BEATEN by beauty from Shami. It is a good length outside off, Hetmyer attempts for a drive but fails to put bat on it.
Jadeja bowls this shorter and on middle and off, Holder blocks it out.
Outside off this time by RJ, Holder leaves it alone.
Full and floated towards middle and leg, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Another one full and on middle and leg, pushed back by Holder.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Tossed up outside off, driven towards mid off where the fielder does well to stop it.
Length ball outside off, left alone by Shimron.
Another similar ball left alone by Hetmyer.
FOUR! Good length ball wide outside off, Hetmyer crunches this one through covers for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone again by Hetmyer.
Length ball wide outside off, Hetmyer cuts it towards point.

OUT! BOWLED! Hetmyer departs and it has crashed into the middle and off pole. Shami bowls this one just around off, it is drifting into Hetmyer. He looks to drive this through covers but is beaten all ends up. The ball goes between the bat and pad and into the timber. West Indies are 6 down now and in huge trouble.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full and floated outside off, Holder pushes this through covers and takes a single.
On the pads of Hamilton, he flicks this one fine towards the leg side and takes a couple to get off the mark.
Full and floated on the off pole, Hamilton defends it onto the ground.
Outside off, left alone by Hamilton.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region. No runs taken.
Beaten! Holder tries to put bat on ball on this one but is beaten as he does so inside the line.
On the pads of Holder, he flicks it towards backward square leg and takes a couple.
Way wide outside the off stump, Jason leaves it alone.

Shami bowls an inswinger this time. Holder looks to push this towards mid on but misses. It hits the pads of Holder and the Indian players appeal. The umpire denies it. The Indian players think about going over for the review but decide against it. Ball Tracker comes in and shows that this was missing leg. Good decision not to review this one by Indian skipper Kohli.
FOUR! Low full toss on the off pole line and Holder pounces on it as he just pushes it through mid off for a boundary.
Top edged but safe again. Holder looks to pull this one towards the leg side but gets a top edge on it and the ball goes back over the bowler's head as the batters take a couple.
Full and floated on off, driven through mid off by the batsman.
Tossed up on middle and off, pushed towards the leg side.
On the pads of Hamilton, he flicks it towards the leg side.
Good length ball on the pads, the batsman has flicked the ball this time.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Shortish one on middle and off, Hamilton defends it off the back foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Bumrah strikes first ball after returning. It is not the greatest of deliveries as it is on a shorter side outside off, Holder attempts to loft this but the ball gets the top edge of the bat and goes way up in the air. Rohit Sharma, the substitute fielder, takes a simple catch at mid off.
FOUR BYES! Bowls this way down the leg side, Cornwall looks to flick but misses the ball. Pant dives to stop the ball but is unable to as the ball rolls on to the fine leg fence.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Length ball on middle and off, Cornwall blocks it out off the back foot. The crowd roars as Rahkeem defends this one out.
Defended off the back foot by Cornwall again.
End of a successful over by Bumrah. Cornwall blocks this one out off the back foot.
Full and floated on middle and off, Hamilton pushes it out off the front foot.
Wide outside the off pole, Hamilton tries to go for the slash but misses.
Driven towards the mid off region off the front foot.
On the pads of Hamilton, he flicks it towards the leg side.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
Hamilton is beaten on this good length delivery as this has hit him on the thigh pad.
Good length ball on middle and off, Cornwall blocks it out.
This time Cornwall is hit low on the pads as he misses his block.
Another length ball on middle and off, pushed out by Cornwall.

EDGED AND FOUR! Not sure whose catch that was but India surely had a chance there. This was bowled on a length on middle and off, Cornwall looks to block this off the back foot but does so inside the line. He gets a thick outside edge on it and the ball flies between Pant and Rahane at first slip. Pant had shuffled to his left early on and misjudged it while Rahane's dive to his left wasn't enough to reach it. The ball goes through them, and towards the third man fence. Cornwall is off the mark in streaky fashion.
Beaten! Another similar ball but this time no edge by Cornwall.
On the pads of Cornwall, he looks to flick this one but misses to get hit near his tummy. The ball flies fine towards the leg side where the fielder mops up and the batters take a leg bye.
Fuller delivery on middle, Cornwall pushes this to mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahkeem blocks it out.
Loopy ball outside off, Rahkeem plays a drive towards cover.
Flighted delivery on off, Rahkeem pushes this towards cover again.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Jadeja this. Bowls a short delivery which pitched on middle and spun away from the batman. Rahkeem leaves it alone but the ball passes the off stump by a whisker.
Flighted delivery on off, Rahkeem drives this hard but it hits Mayank Agarwal at silly point. He seems to be fine here and will continue to be on the field.
Good length delivery on middle, Cornwall blocks this one out.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Rahkeem looks to defend but fails to put bat on it.
Outside off, left alone by Cornwall.
Short delivery on middle, Cornwall defends the ball off the back foot.
Back of a length delivery around off, Rahkeem blocks it out.
Short ball on middle, Hamilton jumps up to defend it into the ground. With this it is STUMPS ON DAY 2.

Whoa! What a start from Shami! Targets the stumps straightaway. Cornwall looks to flick but is hit straight on the pads. This looked going down the leg side. Shami along with the entire slip cordon puts a loud appeal but umpire is unmoved. Good decision by Kohli by not going for the review as Ball Tracker rolled in to show it was going down the leg side.
Outside off on a good length. Left alone.

Length ball on off and middle, pushed straight down the ground. Shami bends down and gets his hand to the ball which hits the timber at the non-striker's end. Hamilton does well to get back in the crease.
EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball in the channel again, Cornwall gets tempted and goes for the drive but it takes an inside edge which flies to the fine leg fence evading the diving Pant.
Length ball on the pads, worked towards the leg side for a single.
Beaten this time due to the away movement on this one. In the channel on the fullish length this time. Hamilton goes for a defense but is beaten. Pant dives to his right to make the stop.
Bumrah starts with one on middle and leg, Cornwall goes for a flick but is hit on the pads.
Shortish ball on the body this time, pushed towards square leg for a single.
Good length ball around off, blocked towards point.
Beaten! Good length ball in the channel, Hamilton goes for a poke by staying rooted in the crease. The ball goes past the outside edge.
This time he defends nicely by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Length ball in the channel outside off, shapes further away as Hamilton allows the ball to go to Pant behind the wicket.
Beaten again! Shami is bowling beautiful lines. Pitches on a good length and shapes a tad bit away from Cornwall. He goes for an expansive drive but misses it completely. Lucky not to edge that one.
Fullish ball on the pads, Cornwall gets an inside edge while defending it towards mid-wicket for a single.
Length ball this time and it is closer to the off pole. Hamilton stands tall to block it well.
That kept low! Good length ball outside off, Hamilton looks to drive but the ball didn't rise enough.
Good length ball around off, Hamilton walks across to blunt this onto the pitch.
Shortish ball this time. And it comes in with the angle to cut Hamilton into half. He looks to defend this one but the ball sneaks through to Pant. Excellent stuff from Shami.
Good length ball outside off, Cornwall lets it go.
Fuller ball around off, Cornwall goes for the drive but the ball takes a thick outside edge and goes through point and gully towards the third man region. Cornwall gets two.
Shortish ball around off again, blocked nicely this time by Cornwall. Very solid defense from the batsman.
Shortish ball on the pads, worked towards backward square leg for a single.
Wide ball outside off, left alone.
Gets closer in the channel outside off on a good length. Hamilton is tempted and goes for a block towards the off side. The ball whizzes past the outside edge.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shami gets the breakthrough for the Indians. Back of a length ball on the body of Cornwall. It shapes in from a fifth stump line. Cornwall looks to fend it off but the ball lobs towards gully. Rahane runs forward to gobble the ball comfortably. Cornwall couldn't have done much with this delivery. West Indies still trailing by 319 runs. 120 runs away from avoiding the follow-on.
Length ball going down the leg side, Roach goes for a flick but misses. Pant dives to his left to make a half stop. No runs conceded though.
Fullish ball on middle and kept low. Roach gets the willow down in time to push it towards fine leg to take one. He is off the mark with that.
Shortish ball on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball in the channel this time, Hamilton has a poke at it but goes past the outside edge. It swung a long way after passing the batter.
This time he gets right behind the line of the delivery to block it well.
Good length on off, blocked towards point this time.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery. Bumrah bowls a full delivery around off, Roach attempts to defend but is unable to put any bat on it.
Full delivery on off, Roach cuts this past the point fielder for a couple. 100 up for the Windies.
FOUR! Good shot from Roach. Bumrah bowls a half volley outside off, Roach plays a lovely drive towards the cover region for his first boundary of the game.
Short delivery on middle, Roach tries to duck under it but gets hit on the gloves. The ball rolls to the leg side and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, Hamilton shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller ball on the fourth stump line, Roach walks across to jam this one in time towards mid on.
Good length around off this time, blocked towards mid off.
Another solid defense from Roach. Good length ball in the channel, pushed back to the bowler.

FOUR! Flicked nicely. Length ball angled into the batter, Roach glances this nicely and because of the pace of Shami, the ball races to the fine leg fence in no time. Very good looking shot that one from Roach.
Typical fast bowler's trait. Gets hit for a boundary and dishes a bouncer next ball. Roach ducks under it nicely.
Top ball to finish the over. Length ball in the channel this time, Roach goes for a poke to push this towards the off side but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Starts with a fullish ball around off, Hamilton pushes this towards mid off.
Another fuller length ball coming into the pads of Hamilton. He works it towards mid-wicket.
Fuller one outside off this time. Hamilton blocks it off his front foot.
Another  ball coming into the batsman from a good length, blocked comfortably.
Good length ball around off again, blocked with ease.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length around off, Roach looks to drive but the ball takes an inside edge and goes onto hit the pads.
FOUR! Top shot that one. Fuller ball outside off, Roach leans into the drive and creams it through the covers to get a boundary.
Good length outside off, Roach blocks it with ease.
Shortish one around off, blocked off the front foot by Roach.
Fuller ball on middle, pushed straight to mid on.
Shortish ball on the body again. Roach looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the pads.
Beaten! Good length ball outside off. Hamilton goes for a push but the ball shapes a tad bit away to go past the outside edge.
Beaten again! Another ball on a good length in the corridor of uncertainty. Hamilton has another poke to get beaten. No luck for Ishant here.

Induces the outside edge this time but the ball doesn't carry. Top ball again as this is pitched on a good length and shapes away from the soft push of Hamilton. It goes towards KL Rahul at second slip on the bounce.
Another good length ball in the channel on off, this time Hamilton is right behind the line of the ball to block.
Another solid block from Hamilton to this good length ball around off.
This time he pushes this good length ball outside off towards cover and takes a quick single.
Jadeja starts with a quicker one. It is a fuller ball, Hamilton goes for the drive but it takes an outside edge through the slip cordon. The slip fielder fumbles but no run taken.
Wide outside off, left alone.
Blocked coming forward to this loopy ball on off and middle.
Another solid block from Hamilton.
Turn and bounce for Jadeja. Flighted fuller ball, pitches and turns away as Hamilton goes for the drive but misses.
Flighted ball on off, pushed towards cover.
Bouncer outside off, Roach sways away from it.

A surprising review has been taken by Kohli! Another shortish ball around off, Roach stands tall to push it towards the off side but it beats the outside edge. Kohli and co. are thinking of a review all of a sudden and they eventually go for it. It never looked as if there was an edge. Ultra Edge rolls in and confirms the same. This is a very poor review from the Indians. Wonder if Pant had any say in this review.
Short delivery outside off, Roach ducks under it.
Good length ball outside off, Roach goes after the ball but can't get bat on it. This should have been left alone.
Shortish ball on the body this time, pushed towards square leg off his back foot to take a run.
Good length ball around off, blocked back to the bowler nicely by Hamilton.
Flatter outside off, left alone.
Loopy fuller ball this time, Roach works it towards mid-wicket.
Huge appeal from Jadeja but the umpire is unmoved. Pitches this one around off and it turns away. Roach defends it well but Jadeja thinks this was pad first and appeals. Good call from the umpire.
Blocked nicely this time.
Another solid block from Roach off his front foot.
Fuller ball around off, worked towards point.
Full delivery on middle, Hamilton pushes this towards mid on.
Good length ball around off, Hamilton cuts it past cover for a couple. Jadeja runs in from point and cleans it up.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ishant breaks the stand. Shortish length ball outside off, Hamilton is tempted to go for the punch but the ball takes the outside edge and goes straight to skipper Kohli at third slip. He is not going to spill this one. A timely wicket this for India because these two were frustrating them with this stand. Follow-on still on the cards?
Shortish ball into the body of Gabriel. He stands tall and blunts it onto the pitch.
Another short ball on off and middle. Gabriel does well to sway away from it.
And again. Another shortish ball around off, this time Gabriel goes for the push but is beaten. A very good over this one from Ishant.

OUT! CAUGHT! West Indies' innings is done and dusted. Loopy fuller ball from Jadeja. Roach looks to heave this inside out over the covers but all he gets it is a thick outside edge. The ball lobs straight to Mayank Agarwal in the covers. Now, will Kohli enforce the follow-on with a lead of 299 runs?
Starts with a fuller ball on the off stump line, pushed towards cover.
Fuller ball around off, looks to block but gets a thick inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller outside off and it stayed low. Rahul looks to defend by coming forward but is beaten.
Dishes a full toss as he looks for a yorker. Pushed straight to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul shoulders arms.
Good length ball, coming into the batsman. Rahul covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper. Good start from Roach this one.
FOUR! Fullish ball on middle and leg, Agarwal punches this brilliantly down the ground to get off the mark. Top shot that from him.
Fuller ball on middle, looks to work it towards mid on but it takes the the outer half of the bat and goes to cover.
Good length ball in the channel outside off, Agarwal initially looked to play but dropped his hands at the last moment.
Wide outside off this time. He lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside the off stump again, Agarwal blocks off his back foot.
Fuller ball this time, pushed back to the bowler.

EDGY FOUR! Fuller ball outside off, KL goes for a drive through the covers but the ball goes off the outside edge through gully and point. The ball races to the third man fence for a boundary. KL Rahul is off the mark with a boundary as well.
Shortish ball outside off, tapped towards point.
Wide outside off, left alone by Rahul.
Inswinging ball outside off, Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish ball outside off, Rahul goes for the cut but he gets a bottom edge on it and it goes to the keeper on the bounce.
This is wide outside off, KL is not fiddling with this one.
Fullish ball on off, tapped towards cover.
Good length ball, shaping away from Agarwal. He lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball outside off again. Agarwal lets it go to the keeper.
Another good delivery outside off. Rahul sees it go to the keeper.
Slightly fuller than the last ball, tapped straight to the cover fielder.
Short one around off, pushed towards gully.
Shortish ball around off, blocked onto the pitch on the off side.
Slightly fuller this time, pushed towards mid on.
Fuller outside off, KL opens the bat face and guides it through backward point for a single.
BEATEN! Good length outside off, in the channel. Agarwal has a poke but he is lucky to not get an outside edge.
This time he doesn't go for the poke to another good length ball outside off.

OUT! Umpire's call! Roach strikes early for the hosts. Good length ball which comes in with the angle. Agarwal hops to push it towards the leg side but misses and is hit on the pads. Roach and West Indies belt out a huge appeal and the umpire raises his finger. Agarwal has a word with his partner at the non-striker's end regarding taking the review and he goes for it. However, the Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that the ball was clipping the top of middle and leg which means the umpire's decision will not change. Agarwal has to walk back to the pavilion. India are effectively 308 for 1.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Rahul leaves it alone.
Good length delivery way outside off, KL does not fiddle with it and lets it go to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Rahul plays it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery outside off, KL lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery outside the off pole line, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on off, Pujara defends this one to cover.
LEG BYE! Good length ball on the pads, Pujara looks to flick but misses and it goes off his pads towards square leg. The batters take a single.

OHH! Rahul is lucky over here. It is a good length delivery around off, Rahul looks to cut but gets an inside edge onto the pads. The ball rolls off his pads and just misses the off stump by a whisker. It was too close to cut and Rahul survives.
Good length ball on middle, Rahul flicks this to square leg and takes a single.
On a length on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara flicks it to square leg. The batters cross over for a single. Pujara gets off the mark with a single.
Shorter one around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Flatter and quicker outside off, left alone by Pujara.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara comes forward to block but the ball hits him on the gloves and lobs wide off the short leg fielder.
Pushed on middle and leg, Pujara is struck on the pads as he comes forward to block. Possibly hit the bat first and hence a muted appeal.
FOUR! Nicely done! Shorish length outside off, Pujara has enough time to rock back and cut it. The ball races to the fence towards third man.
Loopy ball on off, Pujara looks to block but it goes uppishly towards short cover.
Starts with a good length ball on off and middle, blocked by KL.
Wide outside off, Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Shortish length ball outside off, Rahul covers his stumps and shoulders arms.
Shortish ball on the body, Rahul looks to work it towards the leg side off the back foot but the ball takes outside edge and goes to the third slip fielder on the bounce.
Good length ball outside off, left alone by Rahul.

Ends the over with a good ball. This is on a good length, closer to the off pole. Kl wants to let it go to the keeper but he is late in taking the bat away. The ball takes the under edge and rolls towards the slip cordon. IT IS LUNCH ON DAY 3.
Starts with a loopy delivery on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Short ball on middle, Pujara defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pujara comes down the track to defend but misses. The ball hits the pads of Pujara and goes towards short leg on one bounce.
Floated delivery outside leg, Pujara looks to flick but misses.
The batsman rocks onto the back foot and punches the ball.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rahul defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery around off, Rahul guides it to gully.
On a length on middle which kept a little bit low, Rahul does well to block it out.
Full delivery on off, Rahul pushes this one to mid off.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Rahul defends it off the back foot. Back-to-back maiden overs from the hosts.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara comes down the track and flicks it towards mid-wicket for three runs. Chase runs after it and cleans up before it reaches the ropes.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahul flicks it uppishly which goes towards the short leg fielder on the bounce.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Loopy delivery on middle, KL defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on off, Rahul plays it to cover off the back foot.
Another short delivery on middle, Rahul flicks it to the leg side off the back foot.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Pujara jumps and defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Pujara plays it to cover.
Full delivery around off, Pujara plays a drive towards the cover fielder.
On a length outside the off stump line, Pujara does not feel like fiddling with it and lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Brilliant delivery from Gabriel. It is a back of a length delivery which bounced a little extra. Pujara looks to defend but misses the ball.
Full delivery this time from Gabriel, Pujara drives this back to the bowler. Back-to-back maidens from Gabriel.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahul defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on middle, KL defends it off the back foot.
Floated ball on middle, Rahul flicks it to short leg.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.

Just short of leg slip!  Loopy delivery on middle turning a little, Rahul looks to defend but he gets a fine tickle which falls just short of the leg slip fielder who makes a half stop. No runs taken.
The batsman has worked it off his pads behind square.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
On a length outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery way outside the off stump swinging away from the batsman, Cheteshwar lets it go to the keeper.

NO BALL! Shannon oversteps here. Pujara plays a flick shot off this good length delivery towards the mid-wicket region. Bravo runs after it and stops the ball before it reaches the ropes. That looked as if he was touching the ropes but the third umpire doesn't think that way.
Good length ball outside off, Rahul leaves this one alone.
Full delivery on middle, Rahul pushes it to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Rahul defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Pujara comes down the track and plays it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on middle, Pujara attempts to defend but misses and the ball goes on to hit on the pads of the batsman.
Short ball on middle, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara comes down the track and plays it to mid on.
The batsman works it down the leg side. One run added to the total.
Short delivery on middle, Rahul flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara looks to block but it goes off the inner half of his bat towards mid-wicket for a single.
Shannon loses the line a bit here, bowls a good length delivery outside leg, Rahul leaves it alone.
NO BALL! FOUR BYES! Poor bowling from Gabriel. It is a short delivery outside leg, Rahul leaves it alone. Hamilton dives to save the ball but is unable to do so. It runs off to the fine leg fence.
Good length delivery on middle, Rahul blocks it out towards point.
Good length delivery on middle, KL defends the back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Rahul blocks it out off the back foot.
On a length outside off, Rahul leaves it alone to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara comes down the track and works it towards square leg.
Another full delivery on middle, Pujara again dances down the track and flicks it to mid-wicket for a couple.
EDGED AND FOUR! Floated delivery on off, Pujara comes down the track and tries to defend but he gets an outside edge past the slip fielder and the ball goes into the third man fence.
That ball has struck the batsman on the thigh-pad.
Full delivery down the leg side stump line, Pujara leaves it alone.
Looped up ball on middle, Pujara flicks it to square leg.
Good length ball outside off, KL shoulders arms.
Good length ball way outside the off stump line, Rahul leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Roach. Bowls a full delivery around off, Rahul attempts to defend but gets beaten due to the swing on it.
Good length delivery outside off, Rahul lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Rahul plays this one to cover.
On a length outside off, Rahul does not fiddle with it and allows it to go back to the keeper.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pujara dances down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on middle, Pujara blocks it out.
Flighted delivery around off, Pujara comes down the the track to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Another flighted delivery on off, Pujara again comes down the pitch to defend but gets hit on the pads in an attempt to defend it.
Flighted delivery on off, Pujara looks to leave it but it hits the pads and it goes for a four. but it has been signaled as a dead ball as no shot was offered.
Short ball on middle, Pujara flicks it to square leg.

OUT! CAUGHT! Brilliant bowling from Roach. It is a good length delivery outside off, Rahul attempts to defend but gets a thick outside edge back to the keeper who takes a simple catch. Rahul was looking fidgety out in the middle and he perishes.

OUT! CAUGHT! And Kohli goes for a golden duck, his fourth in Tests. Back-to-back wickets for Roach. It is another good length ball outside off, Kohli looks to defend but can only edge it back to the keeper. Excellent bowling from Roach here. He will be on a hat-trick the next ball. Very rare of Kohli to get out for a golden duck. With that wicket, Roach goes past Wes Hall to become 9th leading wicket taker for West Indies in Tests.

EDGED AND FOUR! Rahane survives the hat-trick ball but just. It is a good length ball on off, Rahane looks to guide it but gets a thick inside edge which goes just past the stumps and into the fine leg fence. He is off the mark with this boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on off, Rahane guides this to third man and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara leaves it alone.
FOUR! Beautifully played from Rahane. It is a flighted delivery on off, Rahane comes down the track and drives it straight down the ground for a boundary.
Floated delivery on off, Rahane attempts to defend but gets an inside edge towards short leg where the fielder collects it on the bounce.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Flighted delivery on off, Ajinkya blocks it out.
Loopy delivery on middle, Rahane drives this to mid off.
LEG BYE! It is a flighted delivery on middle, Rahane looks to flick but gets hit on the pads which goes past the short fine leg fielder. The batters take a leg bye.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot towards point.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rahane pushes this to cover.
On a length on the off stump line, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball outside off swinging into the batsman, Rahane leaves it alone but it is very close to the stumps. Excellent delivery from Roach.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Rahane does not fiddle it and leaves it alone.
Loopy delivery on off, Pujara comes down the track and pads this one.
Loopy delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to square leg and takes a single. They think of the second run but decide against it.
Floated delivery on middle, Rahane blocks it out.
Looped up ball on middle, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Rahane comes down the track to this loopy ball and defends it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahane defends it back off the front foot.
Full length delivery on middle, Pujara flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball outside off, Rahane leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara attempts to defend but gets an outside edge towards third slip. He played it with soft hands.
FOUR! Poor delivery from Roach this time. Bowls this on the pads, Pujara likes it there and flicks it towards the fine leg region for a boundary. With this boundary, India's lead goes past 350.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
Another one on a length outside off, Cheteshwar leaves it alone again.
Full delivery on middle, Rahane flicks it to mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Rahane looks to flick but gets a leading edge back to the keeper. Cornwall collects it on the bounce.
Floated ball on off, Rahane comes down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Looped up ball on off, Rahane plays this drive towards mid off.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahane flicks it to the leg side and takes a single.

EDGED BUT SHORT!  Good length ball on off, Rahane attempts to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards second slip. The ball falls short and goes behind the first slip fielder from where Cornwall hares after it and cleans it up.  The batters take a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Pujara defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery down the leg side, Pujara attempts to flick but misses.
On a length outside off, Pujara lets it go.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara plays this to mid on.
Full delivery on middle, Rahane comes down the track and flicks it towards hort leg. It bounces in front off him.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Short ball outside off, Rahane defends it off the back foot towards the off side.

NOT OUT! Rahane survives. It is a flighted delivery on middle,  Rahane comes down the track and looks to defend but misses it. The ball goes off the pads to the keeper. The fielder appeals for a possible bat and pad but the umpire is unmoved. After some thought, The Windies goes for a review. The replays roll in and the Ultra Edge shows that the ball did not hit the bat. West Indies lose a review here.
Flighted ball around off, pushed towards mid off for a run.
Shortish one this time, Pujara goes back and punches it through cover-point. It was a gentle punch and hence can't reach to the fence. Three runs taken.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms as he sees the ball shaping away.
Another one outside off on a good length, left alone by Pujara.
And another one in the same channel outside off, Pujara is not bothered.
Full delivery outside the off stump line, Pujara leaves it alone.
Good length delivery on middle, Pujara defends it off the front foot.

OUT! CAUGHT! Holder strikes here. Pujara's poor series comes to an end. It is a good length delivery outside off which bounces just a little bit. Pujara attempts to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards third slip. Shamarh Brooks takes a good catch. India are effectively 356 for 4.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, comes down the track to push it back to the bowler.
He again dances down the track to this loopy ball to push it towards mid on.
Flatter one on middle, tapped onto the pitch.
Another flighted ball on middle, Rahane gets out of the crease to push towards Cornwall sticks his right hand out to stop the ball.
Shortish length on the pads this time, Rahane blunts it towards square leg.
Another one on the pads, tucked towards the leg side.
Short ball aimed at the body, Vihari ducks under it.
BEATEN! Beautiful from Holder. Another good length delivery around the fourth stump line, Vihari looks to defend but fails to put bat on it.
Full delivery outside off, Vihari shoulders arms to this one.
Good length delivery on middle, Vihari defends it to the leg side off the front foot.
On a length on the middle stump line, Hanuma defends it off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Vihari pushes this one to mid on. Another good over from the Windies skipper, Holder.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahane comes down the track and defends it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on middle, Rahane blocks it out.
Floated delivery on middle, Rahane dances down the track and plays it back to the bowler.
Short ball on middle, Rahane rocks back and pulls it past the square leg fielder for a couple. First runs after three consecutive maiden overs for India.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahane defends it out.
Good length delivery on off, Vihari defends it to point.

Back of a length delivery around off, Vihari attempts to defend but gets an edge towards the third slip fielder who takes it on a bounce. Hanuma played it with soft hands and thats why it did not carry to the fielder at third slip.
Good length delivery on off, Hanuma blocks it out to point.
On a good length outside off, Vihari leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Hanuma shoulders his arms to this one.
Full delivery on middle, Hanuma blocks it back to the bowler.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Short delivery on middle, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
The batsman dances down the track.
Full on middle, Rahane pushes it to mid on.
Flighted delivery on middle, Rahane comes down the track and defends it to short leg.
Floated delivery on middle, Rahane attempts to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards short leg. The ball just passes the short leg fielder.

Good length delivery outside off, Vihari plays a lovely drive towards the cover region for three. Keemo Paul, the substitute fielder, runs behind it and makes an excellent diving stop before it reaches the ropes. Saved a run there.
Good length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
On a length outside off, Rahane shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot towards cover.

Short delivery around off, Rahane slaps it hard towards the point fielder who dives to make the stop but gets a hand on it. The ball rolls on towards the cover fence but is stopped by the cover fielder. The batters take two in the meantime.

SIX! First maximum of the innings. It is a short ball on the leg stump line, Rahane attempts to pull but is not in full control of it. It goes off the top edge and the ball flies over the fine leg fence.
Flighted on middle, Pujara blunts it towards the leg side.
Another loopy ball on middle and leg, Vihari comes forward and pushes it towards mid-wicket.
Shortish one turning down log, helped towards the leg slip fielder.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Huge appeal but not given. Fuller ball on middle, Vihari comes forward to block but is hit on the pads. No review taken by the West Indies.
Flighted ball on middle and leg, Vihari goes for the sweep but can't get bat on ball. The ball flies off his pads over skipper Jason Holder at leg slip.They take 2 leg byes.
Back of a length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls this hard towards fine leg and takes a single.
Good length delivery on middle, Vihari flicks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Hanuma shoulders arms to this one.
On a good length on middle, Vihari defends it off the back foot back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Vihari drives this to mid off. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 3.
Flighted ball on middle, pushed towards mid on.
Loopy ball on middle, blocked on the leg side, closer to the short leg fielder.
Shortish ball, worked towards mid on.
The batsman defends it from within the crease.
Quicker on around off, blocked nicely.
Flighted ball around middle and leg, tucked towards the leg side. Maiden to start the third session.
Good length ball around off, Vihari blocks it well towards the off side.
Fullish ball on off, driven straight to Roach.
Slightly fuller, driven straight to mid off.
Good length ball coming into the body, pushed towards mid-wicket.
FOUR! Crunched through gully. Good length ball outside off. Vihari rocks back and cuts it nicely towards the third man fence. First boundary of the session.
Good length ball closer to the off pole line, Vihari has a poke but the ball goes past the outside edge.
Loopy ball on middle, Rahane goes for the sweep but finds Jason Holder at leg slip who attempts a run out but misses the stumps. Rahane was never out of the crease though.
FOUR! Rahane comes down the track to lift this over mid-wicket but he gets an inside edge and the ball goes towards the square leg fence. The fielder chases but the ball wins the race.
Rahane again comes down the track and pushes this back to Cornwall.
Shortish length this time, tapped towards point by Rahane.
Pushed back to the bowler by dancing down the track.
Shortish ball on the pads, Rahane goes for the pull but finds the fielder. Didn't time it well.
Back of a length ball around off, blocked nicely.
FOUR! Crunched! Fullish ball on the pads of Vihari who flicks this superbly. The ball races through the mid-wicket fence.
Good length ball outside off, tapped towards point.
Wide outside off this time, Vihari lets it go.
Good length ball around off again, blocked towards cover.
Another good length ball but this is on middle, worked towards the leg side.
Flighted ball on off, pushed towards cover for a run.

Huge appeal but it dies down instantly. Fuller ball around off, Vihari looks to work it down the leg side but is hit on the pads. Looked close to the bat and hence the appeal was ignored by the umpire.
Shortish ball, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Loopy fuller ball, Vihari looks to drive but gets an outside edge towards gully.

FOUR! Loopy ball down the leg side, Vihari goes for the sweep but it hits the gloves and goes past Jason Holder in the second slip and through to the fine leg fence. The replays show that it went off the pads of Vihari.
Loopy ball around off, pushed towards cover by Vihari and he calls for a quick single. Brathwaite has a shy at the non-striker's end but he misses. That could've been a risky run.
Full delivery on off, Vihari pushes it to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Vihari blocks it out off the back foot.
FOUR! Shot. Full delivery on middle, Vihari pushes this beautifully past the mid on fielder for a boundary. Excellent batting this.
Good length ball closer to the off stump, blocked towards the off side.
Good length ball outside off, left alone this time by Vihari.
FOUR! Driven down the ground. Fullish ball on middle and leg, Vihari drives this firmly through mid on to get the second boundary of the over. Nobody moved.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
FOUR! Comes down the track to  lift it over mid-wicket but he mistimes it and the ball goes towards the square leg fence.100 up for India with this boundary.
Fuller on off, pushed towards cover for a single.
Flighted ball turning down the leg side. It goes past the flick of Vihari and to Jason Holder at leg slip.
Shortish one this time, worked towards square leg for a single.
Rahane dances down the track and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted ball on off, pushed towards mid off.
Flighted ball on off, tapped towards point.
Loopy ball on middle, swept firmly but straight to mid-wicket.

Nice footwork from Gabriel there to save a couple. Fullish ball on the pads, Vihari sweeps it fine down the leg side. The batsman take a couple as Gabriel hares from the deep to stop the boundary. 50-run partnership comes up between the two.
Flighted ball on middle, worked towards mid-wicket for a run.

Shortish ball on the body, Rahane looks to work it on the leg side but the ball rises a bit and hits him high on the bat. It goes past the short leg fielder. By the time the fielder cleans up, the batters take a couple.
Loopy ball on middle, driven towards mid on for a single.
Short ball down the leg side, worked towards square leg for a single.
FOUR! Tossed up ball on middle, Vihari slog sweeps this towards mid-wicket for another boundary.
This is fired on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Another ball worked towards mid-wicket for a run.
A short delivery which has been pulled away. The batsmen have run through for a single.

Tough chance for Hetmyer! Vihari comes down the track to work it down the leg side but the ball rises a bit. It hits him on the gloves and lobs towards the short leg fielder. Hetmyer comes forward to catch, gets his left hand but can't hold on.
Fuller ball on off, drives firmly towards mid off. A run taken.
Blocked off his back foot this time by Rahane.
FOUR! Fuller ball on middle, Rahane comes down the track and times this over the mid-wicket fence for another boundary. Indians on the charge.
Pushed back to the bowler by Rahane this time.
The batsman dances down the track and pushes this to long off. The batsmen have run through for a single.
Good length ball around off, Rahane defends it off the back foot.
Good length ball on middle, Rahane flicks it to square leg and takes a single.

Good length ball around off, Vihari defends it off the front foot into the ground and takes off for a single. Holder tries to hit the stumps with his boot. It would not have mattered as Rahane was well in.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane pushes it to point.
Good length ball on middle, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Fuller ball on middle, Vihari goes to power this over the long on fence but mistimes. The ball goes towards long on. They take a run.

Dropped! Fuller again, Rahane goes for the sweep and connects well but this is flat and goes towards Shannon Gabriel who is positioned at deep square leg. Gabriel dives forward but can't hold on. Single taken.
FOUR! Short and wide outside off, Vihari cuts is firmly through point for another boundary.
The batsman gets to the pitch of the ball and connects. They pick up a single.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman.
FOUR! Fuller ball outside off, Rahane leans into the drive and creams this through covers for another boundary.
Short one to start wish, Vihari pulls this firmly through the square leg fence for another boundary. Runs coming thick and fast.
Fuller one on the pads, worked towards mid-wicket for a couple of runs.
Blocked by lunging forward this time by Vihari.
Fuller ball, worked towards square leg for a single to get his half ton.  Two in two in the match. A top half century from Vihari this one.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Worked towards fine leg this time for a single. Rahane moves to 49.
FOUR! Half century for Rahane as well. Fullish ball outside off. Rahane goes for the drive but it takes the outside edge flies through gully and second slip to the third man fence.
Played through mid-wicket by the batsman. One run added to the total. The lead is 450 now with that run.
Shorter one on the body, Viahri looks to work it down the leg side but can't time it well. The ball goes to the fine leg for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Beaten after ages. Good length ball in the channel. Rahane has a poke but it goes past the outside edge.
This one is going down the leg side. Rahane looks to flick but misses.
Loopy ball on off, clipped towards mid-wicket.
FOUR BYES! Fuller ball on middle and leg and turns further down the leg side. Vihari looks to work it down the leg side but can't get bat on ball. It races to the fine leg fence for four byes.
Shortish ball, Vihari looks to cut but he gets an outside edge toward third man. They take a run which brings 100-run stand between the two.
FOUR! Rahane comes down the track and times the cover drive sweetly to get another boundary.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. The batsmen have run through for a single.
The batsman flicks it away with a wristy shot.
Good length ball outside off, Rahane looks to block but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Shortish ball on middle and leg, Rahane dances down the track again to have a slog but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Fuller ball around off, Rahane looks to guide this towards third man but is beaten.
Fuller ball around off again, blocked off his front foot.
Fuller ball on the pads, Rahane works it towards mid-wicket for a couple.
On the pads this time, worked towards square leg for a run.
Short and wide from round the wicket from Cornwall, Rahane pushes this through covers for a single.
Fuller on the pads, nudged towards the leg side.
Another one on the pads, worked towards fine leg.
Short outside off, tapped straight to short third man.
Fuller ball, comes down the track to push this through long on for a single.
The batsman has played it towards mid-wicket. They pick up a single.
Fullish ball outside off, driven straight to the cover fielder.
Good length ball on the pads, pushed towards mid-wicket.
Goes past the outside edge. Good length ball in the channel outside off,  Rahane looks to defend but is beaten.
Another good length ball on off, blocked onto the pitch. And Kohli calls his men back to the pavilion. India lead by 467 runs.
Good length ball on the hips of Campbell. He works it towards mid-wicket for a run. He is off the mark on the first ball. West Indies are underway.
Good length ball on off, pushed to covers for a single. Brathwaite is off the mark on the first ball too.
Fuller ball this time, tapped towards point by Campbell.
Fuller ball on off, pushed towards mid off for a run.
Inswinging ball on middle, worked down to fine leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards point.
Right on the money from the first ball. Good length and closer to the off stump, Brathwaite blocks it well.

Fullish length ball around off, Brathwaite taps it towards cover and goes for a quick single. That was a risky run because you don't take a risk like that against Jadeja. However, he misses his shy at the striker's end.
Shortish ball, around off, cut to point by Campbell.
Hit on the gloves! Good length ball on middle, Campbell looks to work it down the leg side but he is hit on the gloves.
Wide outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Overpitched ball on off, Campbell leans into the drive and slams it down the ground. The ball races to the long off fence.
Good length ball on off, blocked towards the off side.
Good length ball closer to the body, pushed back to the bowler.

OUT! Caught! Ishant draws first blood. That is a jaffa from Ishant and Brathwaite can't do much with that one. Good length ball on off, closer to the batsman. Brathwaite looks to defend by coming forward but the ball shapes a tad bit away. It kisses the outside edge of the bat and goes to Pant behind the wicket. Good start for India. Rishabh Pant becomes the fastest Indian wicketkeeper to reach 50 dismissals in Test cricket.

What a ripper to the new man! Good length ball in the channel again, closer to the body. It again shapes away from the defensive push of Bravo and beats the outside edge. Bravo is a lucky man to be standing there.
This one goes down the leg side. Bravo looks to flick but misses.
Closer to the off pole, pushed back to the bowler. End of a successful over from Ishant.
Shortish ball on off, tapped towards point.

Good length ball on middle and swings into the pads of Campbell. He looks to work it down the leg side but is hit near the box. Bumrah has a tendency to swing the ball both ways and most of the times, it troubles the batsmen.
Good length in the channel, left alone.
Good length ball around off, Campbell gets an outside edge in an attempt to defend it towards point for a single.
Fuller ball around off, Bravo drives it through covers to get off the mark with a couple.
FOUR! Fuller again but this one is on the pads. Bravo whips it through mid-wicket for a boundary. An expensive over for India.
Good length ball on off, pushed towards mid off.
FOUR! Good length ball outside off, Campbell lifts this over point and the ball races to the fence. A top shot this from him.
Good length ball on middle, Campbell looks to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
FOUR BYES! Ishant sprays this one down the leg side and it goes further away from Pant. Pant dives to his right to stop that but it is too far away from him. The ball goes to the fine leg fence.
Another one going down the leg side by a big margin. Pant does well to stick his right hand to stop it this time.

Edged and Dropped! Good length ball around off, Campbell has a poke but gets an outside edge and it goes towards Vihari at first slip. He spills it down. However, Pant moved to his left and that could've been the distraction.
Full and wide ball to start, Bravo goes for the drive away from the body. He manages to clear Agarwal at point and get a couple.
Beaten this time. Good length outside off, but lower bounce on it. Bravo can't get bat on ball this time.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
FOUR! Fuller on the pads this time from Shami. Bravo glances this to the fine leg fence. Bravo on the attack mode it seems.
Wide outside off this time, left alone.
Outside off again, left alone by Bravo.
Good length ball from Ishant to start the new over. It is wide outside off. Campbell leaves it alone.
Another good length ball in the channel outside off. Campbell covers his stumps and lets it go to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, JC looks to cut but underedges it and the ball rolls towards the keeper.
Shortish ball on middle, Campbell swivels to pull this through mid-wicket. Bumrah gives it a chase and keeps it down to three.
Fuller on the pads this time, whipped through mid-wicket for a brace.
Fuller ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball outside off, Campbell works it behind point for a couple this time.
Fuller on off, pushed towards point this time.
Gets closer to the stumps on a fuller length. Campbell blocks it well towards mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Shami strikes! Campbell has thrown it away. Fuller ball outside off, Campbell goes for a mighty drive through the covers but the ball takes the outside edge and flies straight to skipper Kohli at third slip. He is not going to drop this one. Campbell should have left this alone but he threw his bat and his wicket eventually.
Good length ball angled into the batsman, Brooks gets behind the line of the ball to block.
This one is fuller on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler by Brooks this time.
FOUR! Whipped nicely. Fullish ball on the pads as Bumrah wants to hit the bull's eye. Bravo whips this one to the mid-wicket fence with disdain.
Wide outside off, left alone by Bravo this time.
Another ball in the channel outside off, left alone.
Beaten! Good length ball closer to the off pole line this time from Bumrah. It straightens a bit and sneaks past the outside edge.
Wide outside off, Bravo shoulders arms to this one.
Good length on off this time. Bravo blocks it well.
Shami sprays this one down the leg side. Pant dives and sticks his left hand and saves four.
Fuller ball outside off, Brooks looks to push this towards cover but it beats the outside edge. There is an appeal but a muted one as they realized it was the bat hitting the turf.
Good length ball in the channel outside off, this time Brooks lets it go.
Another ball outside off on a good length, Brooks shoulders arms.
This time Shami gets closer to the off pole. However, Brooks covers his stumps and lets it go.
Good length ball on off, blocked onto the pitch towards the leg side.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Another ball outside off, Bravo leaves it alone.
Goes past the outside edge this time. Goes over the wicket and dishes a good length ball on middle. This shapes away just a tad bit to beat the outside edge.
Bumper down the leg side, Bravo ducks under it.
OHH! Fuller ball on off, Bravo looks to leave the ball to the keeper but he is late in doing so. The ball goes onto hit the toe end of the bat and rolls towards gully.
Bouncer on the body this time. Bravo ducks under it awkwardly.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Brooks is off the mark with a superb boundary. Fullish ball on off, Brooks leans into the drive and powers it down the ground for a boundary.
This one is going down the leg side. Brooks looks to flick but misses.
Good length ball, angled into the batter, blocked off his back foot.
Goes past the outside edge this time. Dishes on a good length ball and makes it shape a bit away. Brooks goes for the push but missed to get the bat on ball.
Good length ball outside off, left alone.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Bravo looks to block but it takes the outside edge and goes towards Rahane at gully on the bounce.
Good length outside off, pushed straight to cover. Wanted a run initially but decided against it in the end.
Bumper but this is too high and it angles away. Bravo does well to sway away.

Nasty! What a bumper this one. Back of a length ball on the body again, Bravo is not sure if he wants to duck or sway away. He closes his eyes as the ball comes close. He is hit flush on the helmet. The Indian players surround him to check if he is okay.
Bumrah continues bowling back of a length ball. But this one is sprayed down the leg side. Bravo ducks under it well.

Whoa! Almost a wicket off the last ball! Perfect planning from Bumrah as he rattled Bravo with back-to-back bouncers and then dished a wide fuller ball. The sucker ball one can say. Bravo goes after it but misses to get bat on ball. This was a very risky shot and if you add the fact that this was the last ball of the day, there was no need to go after the ball like that. Anyway, STUMPS ON DAY 3!
FOUR! Good start from Brooks on Day 4. Shami bowls a low full around off, Shamarh plays a lovely drive towards the cover region for a boundary.
Good length delivery way outside off, Brooks leaves this alone.
Back of a length delivery around off, Shamarh lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery on middle, Brooks plays it back to the bowler. Better line and length this from Shami.
Another good length delivery which is way outside off, Brooks shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Much better from Shami. Back of a length delivery around off, Brooks attempts to defend off the back foot but misses due to the swing on it.
Outside off, left alone. It did not carry back to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Bravo blocks it towards cover.
On a length outside the off stump line, Darren shoulders arms to this one.
BEATEN! Brilliant delivery from Bumrah. Bowls it on a length outside off, Bravo attempts to defend but fails to put bat on it.
LEG BYE! Back of a length delivery on the leg stump line, Bravo looks to flick but is hit on the pads. The ball rolls towards square leg and they take a single. 50 up for the Windies.
Good length delivery on off swinging into the batsman, Brooks flicks it to square leg.
Good length delivery outside off, Bravo does not fiddle with it and lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Good ball from Shami. It is a good length ball outside off, Bravo attempts to defend but misses it.

Full delivery on middle, Bravo blocks it back to the bowler. Clever bowling from Shami as he bowled two good lengths before this  which he left alone. Goes for a fuller one in order to catch Bravo by surprise but Darren is ready and blocks it out.
Good length delivery on middle, Darren defends it to cover and takes off for a quick single.
BEATEN! Beauty. Good length ball around off, Brooks looks to block it but fails to put any bat on it. Shami is bowling testing lengths here.
PLAY AND A MISS! Another excellent delivery. Shami bowls a back of a length delivery outside off, Brooks looks to defend but misses it again. Good over from Shami comes to an end.
FOUR! Crisply driven! Fuller and on off, Bravo leans into it and creams it through covers. The ball races away to the fence.
LEG BYE! Full delivery on off shaping into the batsman, Roston looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to square leg and the batters take a single.
BEATEN! Beautiful delivery from Bumrah. Good length ball outside off, Brooks attempts to block it but misses it due to the swing on it.
On a length on middle, Brooks defends it back to the bowler.
Good length ball down the leg side, Shamarh looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length delivery around off, Brooks shoulders arms to this one.
