Good length ball way outside off, Chase does not feel the need to play at it and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Chase attempts to defend but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg. The batters take a single.
On a length on the fourth stump line, Brooks lets it go to the keeper.
BEATEN! Excllent bowling from Shami. After three good length deliveries, bowls a full delivery outside off tempting Brooks to drive but he fails to put bat on it.

OHH! Another good ball from Shami. Back of a length ball on off swinging into the batsman, Brooks looks to defend but misses. It hits the pads of the batsman. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. Ball Tracker rolls in and it shows that it was umpire's call.
BEATEN! Beautiful. Shami has Brooks in all kinds of trouble here. Another good length delivery outside off, Brooks once again attempts to defend but misses to put bat on it.
Good length delivery on middle, Chase blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Chase blocks it out.
BEATEN! Good ball. It is a good length delivery outside off, Chase attempts to defend but misses. Lucky not to get bat on it.
Slightly full from Bumrah this time, Chase pushes this towards the mid off region and takes a couple.
Good length delivery outside off, Chase leaves it alone nicely.
Full delivery on off, Chase defends it to point.

FOUR! Shot from Brooks. This will give him a lot of confidence as he had played and missed a few balls earlier. Shami bowls a full delivery outside off, Brooks plays a lovely drive towards the cover region for a boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Brooks defends this off the back foot.
Good length delivery on the fourth stump line, Brooks shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR BYES! Shami bowls a full delivery way down the leg side, Brooks looks to flick but misses. The ball goes past the diving Pant and into the fine leg fence.
Good length delivery on middle, Brooks flicks it to square leg and crosses over for a single.
On a good length around off, it is kept out.
Full delivery on the pads, Brooks flicks it towards fine leg and takes a single.
Good length ball outside off, Chase leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Chase shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Roston thought of defending it at first but in the end leaves it alone.
Good length delivery outside off, Chase lets it go to the keeper.
Full toss on off, Brooks plays it to mid off.
Flighted delivery on middle, blocked by Brooks.
Full delivery outside off, Brooks plays it to cover.
Loopy delivery on off, Chase blocks it out.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Flighted delivery on off, turning away from the batsman, Brooks attempts to drive but gets an outside edge towards point. A maiden to start by Jadeja.
Good length ball on middle, Chase tries to defend but gets an outside edge towards the slip cordon. The fielder collects it on the bounce. He played it with soft hands there.
BEATEN! Good bowling from Ishant. Bowls a back of a length delivery around off, Chase looks to defend but it goes past the bat of the batsman.
Full delivery on middle, Chase defends it towards mid on.
Full delivery aimed at the off stump line, Chase pushes it back to Ishant.

NOT OUT! Impact is umpire's call and it is also going over! Good length delivery outside off which swung into the batsman, Chase tries to put bat on ball but misses it. The ball hits the pads and Ishant goes for a huge appeal for an LBW. The umpire though is unmoved. Kohli goes for a review. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows that there was no bat. Ball Tracker rolls in and shows that the impact is umpire's call and the ball is going over the stumps. India have lost one review.
Bowls a full delivery down the leg side, Chase looks to flick but misses. The ball goes off the batsman's pads and into the mitts of Rishabh Pant.
Fuller and on off, it is hit to mid off for one.
FOUR! Excellently timed and lovely placement too! This is floated up on off but it is very full. Chase leans into it and opens the face at the very end. Guides it through cover-point for a boundary.

Big turn for Jadeja! He slows it up and lands it outside off, Chase lunges and looks to defend but is beaten by the away turn. Hits the outer part of Pant's glove and lobs over Rahane at first slip. A bye is taken.
On middle, Brooks defends it out.
FOUR! Another lovely boundary! Just beautiful. This is very full once again and on off, Brooks just strokes it gently through covers and bags a boundary.
A dot to end a good over for West Indies. Outside off, it is left alone.
FIVE WIDES! Bouncer way above the batsman's head. Chase does not fiddle with it and the ball goes over Pant's head and into the third man fence.
BEATEN! Better delivery from Ishant. Bowls a good length delivery outside off, Chase looks to defend but fails to put bat on it.
Good length ball around off, Chase leaves it alone.
Full delivery on off, Chase pushes this to mid off.
Good length delivery on middle, Chase flicks it to mid-wicket and takes off for a single.
FOUR! Full delivery on middle, Brooks flicks it nicely towards the fine leg region for a boundary. Brooks is dealing in boundaries here. He has scored 20 runs in boundaries out of his 23 runs.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks leaves this one alone.
Shorter delivery on off, Chase guides it to cover-point.
FOUR! Good shot from Chase, Full delivery outside off, Chase opens the face off his bat and guides this towards the third man region for his second boundary.
Loopy delivery on middle, Chase blocks it out.
Short delivery around off, Chase plays a square cut towards cover.
Outside off, left alone by Chase.
Flighted delivery on off, Chase plays it to point.
Starts outside off and then tails back in. Brooks looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket.
Good length delivery on middle, Brooks defends it back to the bowler.
BEATEN! Good length delivery outside off, Shamarh looks to defend but misses it completely.
FOUR! Poor ball from Ishant. Bowls a full delivery on the pads, Brooks flicks this nicely towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. Brooks is looking really good here.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Shamarh shoulders arms to this one.
On a length outside off, Brooks lets it go to the keeper.
Flighted delivery on off, Chase pushes this to cover.
Outside off, left alone by Chase.
Arm ball on the middle, Chase looks to flick but just gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

OUT! LBW! A flatter delivery on middle, Chase looks to defend but does so outside the line. Maybe for the turn. It goes straight on. Misses the bat and gets hit on the pad. Jadeja goes for a huge appeal. The umpire raises his finger. Chase goes for a review. The replays roll in and Ball Tracker shows that it was umpire's call. West Indies do not lose a review. The resistance shown by this pair has been broken.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot. One run added to the total.
Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer leaves it alone.
On a length outside off, Hetmyer shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball outside off, Hetmyer leaves this back to the keeper.

OUT! CAUGHT! Hetmyer falls off a false shot. Full delivery outside off, Hetmyer goes for an expansive drive but hits it uppishly towards cover. Mayank Agarwal takes a simple catch at cover. Hetmyer can't believe it. It is a soft dismissal. Two wickets in quick succession for India. Hetmyer's poor run with the bat continues. India now 6 wickets away.
Good length ball outside off, Blackwood leaves it alone.
FOUR BYES! Sharma bowls a good length delivery way down the leg side. Blackwood looks to flick but the ball goes into the fine leg fence.
Flatter and outside off, Brooks lets it be.
Another one which is outside off, it pitches and turns away. Brooks offers no shot.
Edgy run! This is tossed up on middle, Brooks goes for the drive. The ball turns away and goes off the outside edge through point for one.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.

Dropped! A tough chance though. It was a big deviation. This is fired on off, it pitches and turns away. Blackwood looks to defend but due to the turn, it goes off the outside edge to the right of Pant. He fails to react in time and it hits the outer half of Pant's glove, then onto his pad and goes on the off side.
On middle, it is worked through square leg for one.
FOUR! Good shot from Blackwood. Full delivery on off, Blackwood plays a lovely drive through the mid off region for a boundary.  First boundary for him.
Outside off, Left alone by Jermaine.
On a length outside off, Blackwood shoulders arms to this one.
FOUR! Crunched! Full delivery way outside off, Blackwood drives this uppishly towards the cover-point fielder for the second boundary of the over.
Good length ball outside off, Jermaine lets it go to the keeper.
Full delivery around off, Blackwood pushes this to point.
Flatter delivery on off, Brooks blocks it out.
Flighted delivery on off, Brooks pushes this to cover.
Full delivery on middle, Shamarh defends it back to the bowler.
Shorter delivery on middle, Brooks drives it to covers and takes a single.
SIX! Good shot from Blackwood. It is a full delivery on middle, Jermaine plays a lofted delivery over the bowlers head for a maximum. First six of the innings.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Outside off, it is left alone.
The batsman chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Fuller and on middle, Brooks works it wide of mid on for one.
On off, it is defended.
Outside off, Blackwood need not play at those.
This one is angled into the batter, Blackwood works it towards mid-wicket for one.
Full delivery on middle, Blackwood defends it off the front foot.
Shorter delivery on middle, Jermain blocks it out.
Fullish delivery on off, Blackwood defends it to point and takes a single.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery on off, Brooks attempts to defend but misses due to the spin on it.
Flatter delivery on middle, Shamarh blocks it out.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Good length ball outside off, Jermaine leaves it alone.
A BIG SHOUT FOR LBW! Good length delivery on middle and leg, Jermaine looks to flick but misses. It hits him on the pads. Shami appeals but the umpire is unmoved.

Another shout for LBW but it has been turned down and a review has been taken. It is a good length delivery on middle and leg, Jermaine looks to flick once again but gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved. Kohli goes a review. The replays roll in and Ultra Edge shows that the ball hit the inside edge off Blackwood's bat. India lose both of their reviews.
Good length delivery on off, Swinging into the batsman, Jermaine looks to flick but gets hit on the pads. The ball rolls to second slip.
FOUR! Good shot from Blackwood. It is a good length delivery on middle, Blackwood flicks it to the mid-wicket region for a boundary.

DROPPED! A half-chance you could say. A good attempt though by Shami. It is a fuller delivery on off, Blackwood drives this hard straight back towards the bowler. Shami sticks his left hand out but is unable to hold on to it. The ball goes to mid off and the batters takes a single. That had to stick but it does not.
Floats it up on middle, it is pushed back to the right of the bowler who fails to stop it and a run is taken.
Tosses it up on off, Brooks drives it to mid off.
This lands outside off and it turns away. Brooks lets it be.
On off and then turning away. Brooks looks to defend but it goes off the outer half towards point.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! No wait... it is a NO BALL! Brooks survives to see another day. Just the luck a batter who is short of runs would have wanted. Jadeja is annoyed and rightly so. He bowls an excellent delivery. It lands on middle and it is flatter. Brooks goes back and looks to defend but the ball turns away. Hits the outside edge of Brooks' bat and goes to first slip where the fielder makes no mistake. Brooks starts walking back but is stopped by the umpire as they want to check the front foot. Replays show that it is over.
A dot to end! Outside off, it is left alone.
Shorter and outside off, Blackwood pushes it towards cover for one.
On the fuller side, Brooks pushes it towards wide mid off for one.
BOUNCER! It is bowled above the head of the batsman, Blackwood lets it go to the keeper.
Good length delivery on middle, Jermaine looks to defend but get a leading edge and it towards the off side.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shami bowls a short delivery outside off, Blackwood guides this nicely towards third man for a boundary.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Blackwood looks to defend but misses and gets hit high on the pads.
FOUR! Good shot from Brooks. Full delivery outside off, Brooks prods forward and drives this towards the cover region for a boundary.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Flatter delivery outside off, Brooks looks to cut but misses the ball completely. The ball cut him in half as the ball kept low a bit there.
Flatter delivery on middle, Brooks flicks this nicely towards the leg side for a single.
On middle, blocked.
Flat delivery on off, Jermaine blocks it to the off side and takes a single.
Floats it up outside off, Blackwood hits it to covers.
Flatter and outside off, Blackwood goes back and guides it down to third man for two.
On middle, this is eased down to long on for one.
This is tossed up on middle, Brooks defends it out.
Another loopy ball on off, Brooks pushes it to mid off.
Flatter and on off, the batter goes back and pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up ball on off, Blackwood defends it off the front foot towards point.
On off, defended.

DROPPED! If you want to call one! This too had to stick in. It is a drop technically. Jadeja floats it up on off, Blackwood drives it hard towards silly point. It hits him as he tries to take evasive action. He then tries to hang onto the ball but it spills out.
On middle, this is kept out.
One more ball on the off pole. Blackwood is solid in defense.

Almost! Blackwood negotiates the last ball before Lunch but by just. This is shorter and quicker and it comes in with the angle. Blackwood gets his bat down right at the end. It goes off the inside edge past the leg pole and down towards fine leg for one. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 4!
Good length ball outside off, Jermaine blocks it onto the ground.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Blackwood defends it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Jermaine blocks this off the back foot towards the off side.
On a length outside off, Blackwood pushes this towards point and takes a single. First run after the Lunch break.
Back of a length delivery around off, Brooks defends it to the off side.
Full delivery outside off, swinging away from the batsman, Brooks looks to defend but it goes past the bat.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery outside off, Blackwood attempts to drive it but misses.
Flatter delivery on off, Blackwood drives this to mid off.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Full delivery on middle, Blackwood defends it off the front foot.
Flighted delivery on off, Blackwood pushes this uppishly towards long off and takes a single.
On off, defended off the front foot.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Blackwood defends it off the back foot.
Good length delivery on off, Blackwood plays this to cover.

Short delivery outside off, Blackwood cuts this towards deep point and crosses over for a single. 50-run stand up between the two. It has been an excellent partnership for the Windies but there is still a long way to go for them.
Good length delivery on off, Brooks defends it to point. Jermaine wants a single and it is taken.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Blackwood pushes this to deep point and takes a single.
Full delivery on the pads, Brooks flicks it towards square leg and takes a single.
This is flatter and on middle, Brooks looks to defend but it goes off the inner half through square leg for one.
Floats it up on off, Blackwood drives it to the man at covers.
This is angled into the batter, JB prods forward and tries to defend but it goes off the inner half towards mid-wicket for one.
The batsman has pushed it to the cover region. One run added to the total.
BEATEN! This is on off and it turns away. The batter looks to defend but is beaten by the spin.
Flatter and outside off, this is guided towards point.
EDGY FOUR! Ishant lands this on a length and around off, Brooks defends inside the line. It goes off the outside edge and in between the first slip fielder and gully for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
This is angled into the batter, Brooks looks to defend but it goes off the inner half towards square leg.
Good length ball on middle, Brooks defends this off the front foot.
Full delivery on middle, Brooks blocks it towards the leg side.
Fullish in length on off, Brooks defends this towards point.
Flighted delivery on off, Blackwood looks to defend at first but gets his bat out at the last moment.
Flatter delivery on middle, Blackwood blocks it out.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted delivery on middle, Jermaine defends it towards the off side.
BEATEN! Flatter delivery around off, Jermaine attempts to defend but misses it.
Flighted delivery on middle, Blackwood defends it out. A maiden over here from Jadeja.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Brooks flicks it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Brooks defends it onto the ground off his back foot.
Back of a length delivery on off, Shamarh blocks it towards cover.
Good length ball around off, Shamarh defends this nicely off the front foot towards the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Brooks looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge towards third slip.
Inswinger from Bumrah this time but it is wide outside off, left alone by the batsman.
Tossed up ball outside off, Blackwood leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Flighted delivery on middle which spun away from the batsman, Jermaine looks to defend but fails to put bat on it.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Full delivery on the middle, Jermaine blocks this one out.
BEATEN! Another flighted delivery around off, Blackwood again attempts to defend but misses the ball due to the spin on it.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
BEATEN! Excellent delivery from Bumrah. It is a good length ball outside off, Brooks attempts to defend but fails to put any bat on it.
Back of a length ball outside off, Brooks lets it go to the keeper.
Shorter delivery on middle, Brooks flicks this to fine leg and takes a single. First run for the hosts after 25 balls.

OUT! CAUGHT! A wicket falls at last. It has taken India 20 overs, probably for the first time in this entire series that they have been made to wait for a wicket. And that is because, this man has just got his first wicket of this innings. Coming to the ball, it is a good length delivery around off, Blackwood pokes at it but gets a thick outside edge back to the keeper. There are some animated scenes around, as both Bumrah and Kohli gesture towards someone in the crowd to keep quiet. End of the 61-run stand.
Back of a length delivery on off, Holder defends this off the back foot.
EDGED AND FOUR! Holder is off the mark with an edgy four. It is a good length ball on middle, Holder looks to flick but gets a leading edge towards the point region for a boundary.
Outside off, it is left alone.
Short! This is on off and it turns away. The batter defends inside the line with soft hands. It goes off the outside edge and falls well short of second slip.

That must have hurt Rahul! This is flatter and on off, Brooks goes back and looks to cut but it goes off the outside edge and on the bounce to the fielder at second slip who makes a sharp stop. It might have stung.

Confusion but safe in the end. Brooks pushes this towards mid off and sets off for the single. But Holder is not interested at all. He takes a late start and Pant yells at Shami to throw the ball to him. But the speedster does not listen and goes at the bowler's end instead. Misses the stumps but even if he had hit, Brooks was well in. Should have gone at Pant's end.
On middle, this is defended.
Flatter and on middle, this is kept out.
Back of a length delivery on middle, Brooks defends it off the back foot.

FOUR! MAIDEN FIFTY FOR BROOKS IN TESTS! Excellent innings this from Brooks here. It is a full delivery on middle, Brooks flicks this towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary. He needs to continue here in order to get close to the target.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks defends it out towards cover.
Good length ball outside off, Brooks shoulders arms to this one.
On a length on off, Brooks defends it off the front foot.
Full delivery on off, Holder drives this towards mid off.
FOUR! Good shot from Holder. It is a full delivery on middle, Holder lofts this straight past the bowler for a boundary. First signs of aggresion from Holder.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for the Windies skipper. Holder plays a chip shot  off this full delivery over the bowler's head. He is looking to unsettle Jadeja here.
Short delivery outside off, Holder cuts it straight to point.

Flatter delivery on middle, Holder looks to flick but gets a leading edge to it which goes towards mid on uppishly but falls short of the mid on fielder. They take off for a single. The fielder has a shy at the stumps but misses.
The batsman has driven that ball straight back.
Outside off and it is on a length. Holder lets it be.
Another length ball outside off, it is left alone.
Goes wide of the crease and angles it into the off pole. Does not bring it back enough to make the batter play.
On a length again, Holder guides it to gully.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Holder plays this off the front foot towards cover. Maiden over by Shami.
Flatter delivery on middle, Brooks defends this back tot the bowler.

OUT! RUN OUT! Lazy, lazy from Brooks and it has cost him his wicket. He played a defensive push off this full delivery towards cover-point and took off for a single but was sent back by Holder. Kohli from cover got to his left, picked it up and threw it off balance at the keeper's end. Voila! A direct hit. The Indian players were not confident as they thought the batsmen was well in but the replays showed otherwise. Brooks was shown to be lazy in getting back and had he stretched a bit, he would have easily got in. Poor stuff. A run out is never the best way to get out (there never is any good way) but when you do not put a price tag on your wicket, you tend to lose respect.
Driven through the covers by the batsman.

OUT! It is a legal delivery! That was touch and go and in the end, it is ruled in the favor of the bowler. Jadeja's celebration says it all. He is a relieved man. He gets his second. Hamilton comes and Hamilton goes. This is a ripper from Jadeja. It lands on middle and then turns away sharply. There is also some extra bounce. Hamilton looks to defend but the ball kisses the glove and lobs to first slip where KL Rahul takes a simple catch. Hamilton who showed good resistance in the first innings, does not stay out for long this time. India are now three wickets away.
Cornwall is off the mark as he pushes it through covers for one.
Holder retains strike by easing it to long on for one.
Full delivery outside off, Holder pushes it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on off, Holder looks to guide it but gets an inside edge towards square leg and takes a single.

OUT! TAKEN! Another one bites the dust! It is all happening very quickly now. From 159 for 4 West Indies have slipped to 180 for 8. This is a top catch from Pant. It is on a length and around off, it jags back in. Cornwall ends up defending outside the line, it goes off the inside edge and to the left of Pant who dives and hangs onto it. Just the two wickets away now are India.

That took off from nowhere! This is on a length and outside off, it pitches and moves away sharply.  There is also extra bounce. The batter leaves it. Pant sticks his right hand out and makes a half-stop. A single is taken as the ball rolls towards third man. Bye signaled.
Good length ball outside off, Holder leaves it alone.
FOUR! Glorious shot from Holder. It is a pitched up ball on off, Holder plays a lovely drive through the long off region for a boundary.
Full delivery on off, Holder pushes it to cover.
The batsman lets the ball go outside his off stump.
On middle, Roach tries to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads. There is a stifled appeal for LBW but are turned down.
On the pads, Roach once again looks to defend but misses to get hit on the pads. An appeal but it is turned down.
This is pushed to mid off.
Tossed up again, Roach strokes it to covers.
Well bowled! This is just outside off, Holder pokes at it and gets beaten.
FOUR! Creamed! This is very full and on off, Holder leans into it and strokes it nicely through covers for a boundary.
Back of a length and on off, this is defended.
FOUR! A full toss and it is put away! It is on the pads, Holder flicks it through deep mid-wicket and it races away. Holder is scoring freely here.

FOUR! Edged, short and a boundary! This is on a length and around off, it straightens. Holder is half-forward as he tries to defend but it goes off the outside edge. It lands short of the diving first slip fielder and a boundary results.
On middle, this is kept out. An expensive over by Shami.
Flighted delivery on off, Roach drives this towards cover.
Full delivery on middle, Roach flicks it to square leg and takes a single.
Flatter delivery on middle, Holder blocks this off the back foot.
Short delivery on middle and leg, Holder looks to flick but misses and the ball hits him high on the pads.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
FOUR! Nice shot from Holder. It is a full delivery on middle and leg, Jason flicks this nicely towards the mid-wicket region for a boundary.
FOUR! Slashed and slashed hard! Roach joins the boundary hitting party! This is a length delivery outside off, Roach throws his bat at it, it goes off the middle and through covers for a boundary.
On a good length and around off, Roach defends it out.
Ouch! That is a stinger! It is a good length ball around off, it shoots off the surface. Roach looks to drive but then misses to get hit high on the elbow. Does not show any pain though.
Fuller and on off, it is driven to mid off.

OUT! No. 9 is out of here! One more time, it is the combination of Pant and Shami which is in play. Shami's third. It is fuller and outside off, Roach looks to drive but gets an outside edge to the keeper. India only a wicket away now.
Fuller and on middle, this is worked towards mid-wicket and a run is not taken.
Holder wants to have some fun! He looks to go big but it goes off the inner half towards mid on for no runs.
Flatter and on off, Holder goes back and keeps it out.
Shorter in length and on off, Holder pushes it down to long off but no runs are taken.
FOUR! Streaky! This is angled into the batter, Holder looks to go for the slog sweep but gets an inside edge past Pant and down to the fine leg fence.

OUT! BOWLED 'EM! End of the Windies innings! Jadeja gets the last man. He fires it on middle, Holder looks to hoick it but misses and the stumps are shattered. All smiles in the Indian camp as THEY WIN BY 257 RUNS AND TAKE THE SERIES 2-0!
